title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Divide mixture in two.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: middle eastern chopped salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pudding has risen about 1/2 inch.
Stir thoroughly and return to oven until firm, about 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup cheese.
Saute onion in small amount oil or margarine.
Combine soup, milk, pimientos, 1 1/2 cups cheese and onion in large pan.
Stir in hash browns.
Pour in oiled 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°. Remove foil, sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: shoe peg corn-vegetable salad
directions: Drain all canned vegetables.
Mix all vegetables together.
Heat sugar, oil, salt and vinegar until sugar has melted.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill thoroughly.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in oil, then drain fat.
Add onions, green onion, bell pepper and garlic to sausage.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Season with salt, black pepper and red pepper.

title: brunch for a bunch - baked eggs
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Spread bread cubes in the bottom of the pan and top with sausage, then cheese. Beat or mix in a blender the eggs, milk, mustard, onion and green pepper. Pour egg mixture over ingredients in pan. Refrigerate 1 hour or overnight.

title: super potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes with jackets and peel while hot.
Cool and cube them.
Mix in green pepper, cheese, salt, milk, pimento, onion and pepper.
Place in a baking dish and pour melted butter on top. Sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
This can be prepared ahead of time, removing from refrigerator at least 3 hours before baking time.
At that time put on butter and parsley.

title: iced coffee
directions: Boil coffee in water until coffee is the desired strength; strain out grounds.
While still hot, add chocolate, sugar and vanilla.
Cool to about room temperature.
Add milk.
Before serving, add ice cream.
Put ice cream in large punch bowl and pour coffee mixture over the ice cream just before serving.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans and cook about 1 hour.
Saute onion and garlic clove.
Pour all ingredients in beans and cook until tender over low heat.
Salsa can be poured over beans and serve with cornbread.
Serve over a bed of rice.

title: meringue miniatures
directions: Combine dry ingredients and mix well. Grease 2 large cookie sheets. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form but not dry. Gradually beat sugar mixture into egg whites, beating 7 to 10 minutes after all the mixture has been added.

title: marian's treats
directions: Mix well the cheese, butter and salt.
Add flour, mixing well, then add Rice Krispies.
Mix and shape into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and mash flat with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Can substitute real bacon bits for beef.

title: chicken-ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water until barely tender. Drain and rinse, then toss with cheese and minced onion.
Using a 3-quart casserole, place 1/3 noodle mixture in casserole.
Make 2 layers of meat with 1/3 noodles between.
End with noodles.
Top with bread crumbs tossed in 2 tablespoons of butter and garlic salt to taste.
Pour about 2 cups of chicken broth over all and bake, covered, in 350° oven about an hour after it begins to bubble.
It should take up the broth.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt butter in large Dutch oven; blend in flour to make a smooth paste and stir in hot water.
Saute beef and drain off drippings; add beef to soup.
Add fresh and frozen vegetables, seasonings and tomatoes (break up tomatoes).
Bring soup to boil, then simmer until vegetables are cooked (about 1 hour or longer). The longer the better.
You may freeze for later use.
Makes about 10 servings.

title: sour cream noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Saute beef in butter.
Add salt, pepper, garlic salt and tomato sauce to meat; simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and noodles.
Place a layer of noodle mixture in a shallow 2-quart casserole; top with meat mixture.
Repeat procedure.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cook pork until brown; season with salt and pepper.
Add barbecue sauce, pineapple juice, vinegar and cornstarch.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Add pineapple chunks and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: lunch box dates
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon-colored.
Beat in sugar and vanilla extract.
Stir together the cracker crumbs, baking powder and salt and mix in.
Add nuts and dates.

title: fiesta pork burritos
directions: Cut pork loin into strips and stir-fry with vegetable oil and onion.
Stir in corn and taco seasoning.
Roll up portions in four warmed flour tortillas and serve with salsa, rice and beans.

title: roast beef supreme
directions: Line a baking pan/dish with aluminum foil.
Salt and pepper roast and place in pan.
Pour 1/2 to 3/4 bottle of A. 1. sauce over meat.
Add one package of dry onion soup mix and top meat with one can of mushroom soup.
Fold ends of foil over the meat, sealing it. Bake in 350° oven for about 3 hours.

title: orange rolls
directions: Open the can and separate the biscuits.
Melt the stick of butter in a bowl.
Place sugar in a shallow bowl.
Dip each biscuit in butter, then roll in sugar, then orange juice.
Place rolls around a large glass pie dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Mix well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Pour in ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sandy's fruit salad
directions: Combine pudding, milk and orange juice concentrate; blend well.
Add sour cream; fold into fruit.
Refrigerate.
Best if served immediately, but not necessary.
Great winter fruit salad.

title: holiday eggnog bread
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Combine eggnog, egg and butter.
Add to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Stir in nuts and fruit; turn into buttered 9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Combine cooked macaroni with next 4 ingredients in large bowl. In saucepan heat soup and milk, then stir in cheese until cheese melts.
Stir into macaroni mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 2-quart casserole dish for 20 minutes at 400° to 425°.
Serves 4.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk and beat well.
Gradually stir flour into creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Chill.
On wax paper or plastic, shape the dough into a long tube shaped roll.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice into rounds 1/4-inch thick.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until edges are slightly brown.

title: smokey mountain dandelion wine
directions: Gather dandelion blossoms, no stems.
Boil blooms with rind and juice of oranges and lemons in the water for 1/2 hour.
Let set for 24 hours, then strain.
Add sugar and yeast.
Leave in a covered crock for 2 weeks, steam again and bottle.
Allow to age.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain the sweet potatoes and heat.
Then add
1 stick of margarine (melted), flour, cinnamon, vanilla, sugar (white), milk, nutmeg and eggs.
Mix this well and pour into a long dish.
Melt the other stick of margarine and mix in the pecans, brown sugar and bourbon.
Spread this over the potato mixture and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes or until set in the center.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Two pie shells (ready made, frozen) are needed.
Pour the mix into the shells and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy-do-fudge
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and milk in large, heavy saucepan.
Over low heat, bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes, stirring to avoid scorching.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir vigorously, making certain all particles are dissolved.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: joan's cheesecake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rack 1/3 way up from bottom of oven.
Beat the cream cheese and butter until smooth and creamy.
Add vanilla, sugar and cornstarch.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, on low speed.
While beating, add cream and juice (batter will be thin).
Pour into pan and place pan into larger pan.
Pour hot water to depth of 1 inch in larger pan.
Place pans in oven for 30 minutes.
Rotate pans and increase temperature to 375° for 15 minutes, or until top is golden brown.
Remove from oven; cool on rack.
May invert onto dish, if desired.

title: pickle rolls
directions: Spread one side of ham with cream cheese.
Place pickle on edge of each ham slice.
Roll ham slice around pickle.
Press edges together to seal.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Cut each pickle into 6 slices.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald the milk.
Put bread crumbs in large casserole; pour scalded milk over the crumbs.
Let cool.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°, or until done.
Test with a toothpick.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and pour on meatballs (drain grease off meatballs if you have any).

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in pie crusts. Keep cool. Makes 2 pies.

title: won ton rolls
directions: Blot sausage dry with paper towels and combine with cheeses, salad dressing, olives and peppers.
Fill won ton wrappers with 1 teaspoon mixture; wet corners of wrappers.
Roll up and fold in corners.
Deep fry at 350° until light brown.

title: salmon pea wiggle
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven or large saucepan.
Add flour and stir until smooth over low heat.
Add milk and heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
After mixture boils and thickens, add peas and salmon.
Cook until peas are done.
Serve over rice, mashed potatoes, biscuits, toast or crackers.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Fry bacon in small pieces, then add onion and pepper.
After tender, add hamburger.
When cooked, drain grease off.
Then add tomato juice and tomato paste.
Cook for 1 hour.
Add mushrooms, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste; simmer for at least another hour.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add yolks one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend in vanilla flavoring and chocolate.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) layer pans lined with wax paper. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost tops only.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar. Stir in peanut butter and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into ready made chocolate pie crust.
Freeze until set.

title: festive onions
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in onions.
Cook, covered on medium low heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and golden, stirring constantly.
Divide onions evenly among 6 (6 ounce) individual casserole or custard cups.
Beat eggs until light.
Stir in half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour atop onions or place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish and pour mixture atop.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until mixture is set (allow 15 to 20 minutes for onions in baking dish).
Sprinkle with cheese last 5 minutes of baking.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter, oil, eggs and sugars until creamy. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Drop by spoonful on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gumbo with crab, shrimp and chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove and make a roux by gradually adding flour to remaining oil.
Cook, stirring constantly over low/medium heat until roux takes color of milk chocolate.
Add ham, onion, green pepper, onion tops, parsley and garlic. Continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add 1/4 cup water, chicken pieces and all seasoning except file powder.
Mix thoroughly. Keep heat low, add remaining water and bring to a boil, stirring gently.
Simmer 45 minutes, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from bones, cut in small pieces and return to pot.
Add shrimp, cook a few minutes.
Add crabmeat, bring to a simmer.
Let simmer die down, add file powder, stir and let stand in pot a few minutes.
Serve over rice in bowls.
Serves six or more.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Mix honey, soy sauce and chili sauce.
Place pork chops in a greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, bread crumbs, eggs, salt, pepper with 1/2 cup catsup or tomatoes.
Be sure to mix well.
Place in casserole dish or small bread pan.
Shape with rounded top.
Put catsup on top of meat loaf.
Cover with foil and cook in a 450° oven for 20 minutes. Then reduce temperature to 250° and cook 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crescent taco pie
directions: Brown meat; add seasoning mix and water.
Simmer 5 minutes. In a 9-inch pie pan, form crust for pie with rolls.
Sprinkle 1/2 of chips on bottom of crust.
Spoon on meat; spread sour cream and cover with cheese.
Sprinkle over the other 1/2 of chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with chopped lettuce, tomatoes and taco sauce.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Combine all and serve with Dressing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix in oil and water.
Blend in pumpkin and eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar for 20 minutes or until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one. Add flour; mix well. Add lemon extract; blend well. Fold in 7-Up. Pour in greased and floured pound cake pan. Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Soak peaches in sugar for 1 hour.
Add orange juice, pulp and cherries.
Cook for 1 hour.
Seal while hot.

title: party chicken
directions: Place slice of beef on breast and roll up.
Wrap with slice of bacon.
Use toothpick to hold.
Arrange in flat baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.
Serves 8 people.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Mix rice and Cheez Whiz in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in broccoli, cook in a preheated 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until hot throughout.

title: apple-nut crunch(microwave)
directions: Combine apple, 1/2 cup brown sugar and lemon juice; toss lightly.
Place mixture in a square baking dish.

title: breast of chicken
directions: Pepper, but do not salt, chicken breasts.
Wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around each chicken breast which has been formed into a small ball.
Place each ball on dried beef in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with mixture of chicken soup, sour cream and cream cheese.
Cover lightly with foil.
Place in 275° oven for 3 hours. Serve on bed of rice.
I double or triple this recipe and freeze in smaller baking dishes.
May be heated in microwave and served on short notice.

title: squash or pumpkin cake
directions: *Pack pumpkin or squash tight and try to get as much water out of it as you can.

title: flo's beef marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar with tight lid.
Shake well to blend.
Pour over roast.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Oven bake or grill, basting with marinade.

title: mopping sauce for barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Then mop on meat.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in other ingredients and drop onto waxed paper.

title: pay a la flojie(lazy cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In bowl, blend cream cheese until creamy.
Add sweet and condensed milk, blend until creamy.
Add in eggs and vanilla, blend thoroughly.
Pour contents into ready-pie crust.
Bake for around 45 to 55 minutes or until golden brown. Garnish with your favorite toppings such as cherries, strawberries or blueberries.
Serves 8 to 10 slices.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak and sort beans overnight.
Drain and add fresh water to cover.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours on stove.
Mix next 7 ingredients together and add to beans while they are cooking.
Add cut up bacon and chopped onion and continue cooking until beans are tender.
Bake in 325° oven for 6 hours or until liquid is gone.
Freezes well.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Put sugar over blueberries and set aside.
Mix lemon juice and condensed milk together and set aside.
Mix together Cool Whip, berries and pecans.
Fold in milk mixture.
Pour in graham cracker crust and chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and moisten with mayonnaise and pineapple juice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
If batter is too thick, add a little water.
Fry in hot shortening.
Drain on paper towels. Enjoy with any meal.

title: chicken a la christy
directions: Mix together and bake, uncovered, at 375° for one hour.
Serve over brown rice or for variation, serve over white rice, noodles, baked potatoes, wild rice, etc.

title: bean and bacon soup
directions: Prepare navy beans according to package directions.
Continue to cook beans.
Add the diced bacon.
If counting fat, cook bacon in microwave, discard bacon drippings and dice bacon.
If bacon taste is desired, dice uncooked bacon and add to cooking beans. Add tomato soup, sauce, diced tomatoes and 2 cans of water. Additional water may be added while cooking.
Add a dash of basil, pepper and oregano.
Simmer soup 2 to 3 hours.
Soup will thicken with cooking.
For thinner soup, add water.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Let margarine soften in a large bowl. Add powdered sugar, vanilla, peanut butter and rice crispies. Mix thoroughly by hand. Make small walnut-sized balls. Put bowl in fridge and chill for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool, then crumble.

title: easy spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger until brown.
While frying, add chopped onion and green pepper.
Drain fat from hamburger.
Add tomato paste and tomato sauce.
Stir to mix.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: irish soda bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix 4 cups flour with the baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and caraway seed.
Add raisins and mix with fingers to separate them.
Add milk and mix with a fork until mixture forms a dough.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup more flour on a board or counter.
Turn out dough and knead for about 5 minutes, working in the flour from the board and forming the dough into a smooth rond loaf.
If sticky, add more flour.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter.
Stir in eggs.
Add soda to buttermilk; add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add orange slices, coconut, dates, pecans and orange peel.
Mix well.
Turn mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake for 2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: greek potato salad
directions: Chop green onion, bell pepper and parsley; slice cooked potatoes.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Use more mayonnaise if needed.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a casserole dish and cover with Cheddar cheese soup.
Bake at 30 minutes at 400°.
Serve with rice. Serves 4.

title: brisket
directions: Put soup mix over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 2-3 hours.
Should be fork tender and very juicy.
Slice thin at angle.

title: codfish and potatoes
directions: Clean codfish well.
Boil and drain.
Clean again.
(Get rid of all salt.)
Boil again until tender.
Boil potatoes (firm).
Cool. In frying pan, add remaining ingredients and stir regularly on medium heat.
Add codfish and potatoes.

title: la vosh
directions: Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing until smooth.
Spread the cream cheese mixture thinly over tortillas. Layer meat, tomatoes and lettuce.
Roll tightly; cut in slices. Chill until ready to use.

title: chocolate squares
directions: 1st Layer (Crust):
Mix 1 cup pecans, 1 1/4 cups flour and 1 1/2 cups melted margarine together.
Spread in sheet cake pan. Cook 10 minutes at 300°.
Cool completely.

title: percolator punch
directions: Use a 30 cup or more automatic coffee maker.
Place first 3 ingredients in the pot.
Place sugar, and spices in basket.
Plug in and perk.
Serve hot.
Remainder may be stored in refrigerator and reheated.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add Cool Whip to mix.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with a layer of crackers (whole).
Pour pudding mix over them, then put another layer of crackers on top.
Melt chocolate, butter, 4 tablespoons milk, powdered sugar and vanilla. After mixing, while still warm, carefully pour over top of crackers and smooth out.
Chill for 8 hours before serving.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix chicken, soup, mushrooms and pimentos. Divide among six 6-ounce custard cups.
Place on cookie sheet.

title: crock-pot reuben spread
directions: Drain, squeeze and chop sauerkraut.
Cut up corned beef and cheese.
Add Thousand Island dressing to first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Put in crock-pot and cook on low for 2 hours.
Spread on crackers or party rye bread.

title: pineapple icing for angel food cake
directions: Mix shortening and butter with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add 2 1/2 cups more powdered sugar and crushed pineapple.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Double recipe for an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix the sour cream and soup together; spread over chicken.
Cover with crackers.
Pour over melted margarine; sprinkle with poppy seed.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: guacamole tomato dip
directions: Peel,
pit
and
dice avocados.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Blend in electric blender until light and fluffy. Chill.
Serve on
lettuce leaves as a salad, as a dip or sauce for some vegetables. Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soups, taco sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Layer meat and then Tostitos, ending with cheese.
Bake until cheese bubbles.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Put all in bowl and mix with electric mixer for 4 minutes. Put into 3 small loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: meat dip
directions: Brown and drain sausage and ground beef.
In a crock-pot, melt cheese with Ro-Tel.
Add meat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: savory stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; cook in boiling salt water 5 minutes.
Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out seed, discard.
Sprinkle inside with salt and pepper.
Melt butter, add meat, celery and onions; cook, stirring until brown.
Add sauce and bread crumbs, mix well.
Spoon mixture into cavity or squash; place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: ruby red dressing
directions: Beat jelly with fork until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat again until smooth.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press dough into pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Cool completely.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla which has been mixed together and spread over dough.
Arrange fruit on cheese mixture.
Mix marmalade and water and put over fruit.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually blend sugar, flour and cocoa. Combine beaten eggs and milk; stir into first mixture.
Cook in top of a double boiler until thick and smooth, stirring frequently.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell and cool. Cover with whipped cream and put in refrigerator.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix with enough butter to make moist. Mix broth and remaining butter with stuffing mixture. Blend soups together with milk. Place 1/2 of dressing mixture in bottom of 10-inch casserole dish. Put chicken over stuffing. Pour soup mixture over chicken. Put rest of stuffing on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix concentrate, cornstarch and cinnamon together and simmer until thick.
Add in apples to coat.
Pour into pie shell and cover with crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add milk; blend in oleo.
Add flour, vanilla and nutmeg.
Make a stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board; cut with cookie cutter.
Grease cookie sheet with oleo. Bake at 325° about 10 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Cook noodles and rinse. Combine remaining ingredients except Mozzarella cheese.
Place half of the noodles, cheese mixture, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Repeat, using remaining ingredients. Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: frosting
directions: Combine butter, sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a full boil and cook 10 minutes.
Then stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts. Frosting thickens as it cools.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Take juice from all three cans of fruit and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Cook juice with pudding.
Cool completely, then add drained fruit and refrigerate.

title: chili beans
directions: In Dutch oven heat oil, add onions and garlic, saute until tender, 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add ground beef and cook until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Add tomatoes, paste, chilies and seasoning.
Simmer, covered, over low heat, stirring occasionally for about 2 hours.
Add drained beans to chili.
Cook until heated through.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for any tossed salad.
Drain and wash chilled beans; add to lettuce.
Add tomatoes, onion and cheese. Add dressing 30 minutes before serving.
Crushed Fritos are added and mixed well immediately before serving, not earlier.
Serves 12.

title: kraut ball
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Drain kraut well.
Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all sausage, kraut and cream cheese by hand. Let chill in fridge for a couple of hours.
Form into balls.
Dip balls into beaten egg, then roll in bread crumbs and parsley. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix coconut and nuts and pour into pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions, using milk instead of water.
Pour on top of coconut and nuts.
Melt margarine and cream cheese.
Add 1 box confectioners sugar and mix well.
Pour this on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add the 2 1/2 cups boiling water to jello.
Put in freezer for about 10 minutes or until jello thickens a little.
Fold whip cream and strawberries in jello, alternating a little bit at a time until mixed well.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Put half of angel food cake in bottom of an 8 x 13-inch pan.
Pour half of mixture over cake.
Layer the other half of cake and pour remaining mixture over top. Let set in refrigerator for about 2 hours before serving.

title: squishy bags
directions: Pour the first 3 ingredients into a pan; stirring constantly, heat them until the mixture thickens.
Cool.
Divide the mixture into 3 separate bowls.
Add one color of food coloring to each container and mix.
Spoon the colors into 1 resealable plastic bag.
Seal it and tape it closed for additional security.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Pour over potatoes.
Use mixer.
Beat well. Add eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon, if desired.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 big pies.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Stir ingredients together until moistened and press firmly in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Press crushed cookies and butter into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream the cheese.
Add pudding.
Spread over crushed cookies.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush the 12 cookies and sprinkle over top.
Chill for several hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into steak.
Brown meat and onion in hot fat.
Add tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat or bake in oven at 350° until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Put chicken into large pot of water.
Cut vegetables to desired size; add to soup.
Cook on low heat for 5 to 6 hours. About 1 hour before serving, remove chicken, debone and take off skin, then put meat back into pot.
Then add tomato sauce and barley.
About 20 minutes before serving, add noodles.

title: fiesta peas and celery
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until veggies are crisp and tender.

title: buffet casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Whisk butter, soup, sour cream and place half of mixture over half of the potatoes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 cup of cheese.
Add the remaining potatoes, spread with the soup mixture; sprinkle with the cheese.
Bake for 50 minutes.
Cover if top gets too brown.

title: desirable cinnamon rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.

title: rice and pork chops
directions: Brown
pork
chops.
Remove
from
pan	and
add 2 cups water, bouillon
cubes and 1 cup rice.
Replace pork chops in pan
and add slices of onion, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Heat the milk, sugar and salt in a double boiler.
Beat the egg yolks slightly, and slowly add some of the heated milk.
Pour back into the double boiler, and stir constantly until the custard coats the spoon.
Remove at once from the fire.
Place the pan in a bowl of cold water, and stir the custard occasionally as it cools.
Add the vanilla.
Grease a baking dish, layer cookies and bananas.
Pour custard over each layer.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns, melted butter, salt, green pepper, chopped onion, cream of chicken soup and grated cheese.
Mix all together well; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: molded chicken loaf
directions: Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup broth.
Melt remaining broth; add gelatin and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add chicken, salt and pepper.
Cook until begins to thicken.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold or loaf pan.
Chill several hours; slice, serve on lettuce and top with tomato slices and green pepper rings.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine and sugar.
Add eggs. Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon and mix well.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 350° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Best served warm with Cool Whip or whipped cream

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Make incision on dark side of flounder.
Remove backbone by carving from center to each side.
With 2 sides slightly separated, remove all remaining bones.

title: party fruit punch
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well; chill.
To serve, combine chilled mixture and ginger ale in a bowl.
Garnish with fruit slices.
Yields 2 gallons

title: meat ball chowder
directions: Put water, soup mix and bouillon cubes in a 4-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer on low heat.
Add rest of ingredients into soup, except beef and garlic.
Mix beef with garlic.
Push heaping tablespoonfuls of beef mixture into hot soup. Simmer until meat balls are no longer pink.
tags: Swiss Knorr tomato soup with basil soup mix

title: angel hair with tomatoes, basil and garlic
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Drain.
Heat oil; add garlic and cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, basil, salt and pepper. Cook for 3 minutes.
Add hot pasta to skillet.
Toss well.
Add chicken broth and stir.
Toss with Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, drop by teaspoon.
Bake 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, brown the meat, half at a time, in hot oil.

In the same saucepan, combine the meat, carrot, onion, tomato sauce, 1/2 cup water, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt. Cover and cook over low heat until the meat is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Blend 1 tablespoon cold water with the cornstarch. Add to the stew.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Serve the stew over the noodles, sprinkled with poppy seed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Take sausage out of casing. Brown ground beef and sausage together. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Let simmer for 45 minutes.
Add paste, simmer about 5 more minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese in greased pan. Place in 350° oven until top cheese melts and bubbly.

title: lemon chicken with capers and nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread the nuts on a piece of foil or baking dish and toast in the oven until golden brown (about 4 minutes).
Set aside and cool.
Gently pound each chicken breast between two pieces of waxed paper until evenly flattened, about 1/4-inch thick.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: grandma stinebaugh's ice tea
directions: Combine water, tea bags, sugar and peppermint.
Bring to boil. Turn off and let set 2 hours.
Squeeze lemons and oranges into a 4-quart pitcher.
After tea sets, take out peppermint and pour into pitcher.
Add 6 cups cold water.
Stir well.
Pour over glass of ice (is the best).

title: gravy smothered minute steak
directions: Salt and pepper steaks. Dip in buttermilk, then into flour. Fry in hot Crisco shortening until brown. Remove steaks from shortening.
Add 1/2 flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth, then add 2 cups water to make a gravy.
Return steaks into gravy and cook about 1 1/2 hours on low heat until tender; turn often.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, brown 1 pound ground beef or turkey.
Add cans of tomato sauce.
Add next three ingredients.
Mix well.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve over warm hamburger buns.
Serves 6.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soups, broth, chilies and onions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer first the tortillas (torn in large strips), chicken, sauce mixture and cheese.
Layer twice.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with side dishes of picante sauce and/or sour cream.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: In a large mixing bowl, blend ingredients and mix with electric mixer on high speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Place in freezer.
Freeze according to freezer instructions.

title: barbecue sausage bites
directions: In a 3-qt. slow cooker, combine the sausages.
In a small bowl, whisk the barbecue sauce, marmalade, mustard and allspice.
Pour over sausage mixture; stir to coat.
Cover and cook on high for 2-1/2 to 3 hours or until heated through.
Stir in pineapple. Serve with toothpicks.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice and mandarin orange juice into saucepan and heat.
When hot (do not boil) add box of vanilla pudding and pie filling.
Mix well and cook until thickened.
Set aside to cool and then stir in the pineapple tidbits and mandarin oranges. Refrigerate.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk and blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and
chill until firm.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except apricot preserves.
Pat in about 2/3 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread apricot preserves over top of mixture.
Put the remainder of mixture on top of apricot preserves.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry big top
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: zucchini mustard pie
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender (estimated 10 minutes). Stir in parsley and seasonings. Blend eggs and cheese in a large bowl. Stir in zucchini mixture. Separate rolls into 8 triangles. Press onto bottom and sides of 8 x 12 baking dish to form a crust. Spread mustard all over crust. Pour zucchini mixture into crust. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes (until knife inserted in center comes out clean). Let cool 10 minutes. Cut into wedges to serve.

title: chili egg puff
directions: Beat eggs until creamy.
Add everything, except chilies, to eggs.
Add chilies last.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine next 3 ingredients; mix to pancake consistency.
Pour over peaches evenly.
In seperate bowl combine cornstarch and sugar; sprinkle over cobbler.
Pour water on top and bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Reserve 2/3 cup broth.
Bone and coarsely shred chicken and set aside.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
sugar; add egg yolks and beat until creamy.
Sift
flour
and
salt together three times.
Combine soda
and sour cream.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream mixture
to
the butter, sugar and egg mixture.
Stir in vanilla and almond extract.
Fold in egg whites that have been beaten
until
stiff.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: calico bean casserole
directions: Dice and brown bacon with onion.
Brown ground beef.
Combine the rest of the ingredients together with the meat, bacon and onions.
Place in a large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split banana bread
directions: In large bowl cream sugar, egg and butter with electric mixer until fluffy, about 3 minutes.
Set aside.
In small bowl, mix bananas and milk (to which I add 1 tablespoon vinegar); set aside. Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda onto paper plate or bowl.
Add dry ingredients to creamed butter mixture alternately with banana mixture, stirring with spatula until all dry ingredients are blended, about 1 minute.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon into greased and floured bread pan.
Drop pan twice from 6-inch height to countertop to remove air bubbles or let rest 20 minutes before putting into oven.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes before removing to rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: liquid fertilizer
directions: Dissolve in one (1) gallon of water and shake before each use. It is a good liquid fertilizer for container grown plants.
May be made with ingredients found around the house or easily obtained from the drug store.

title: reuben baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 425° for 45 minutes or until tender. Cool in a bowl.
Combine the corned beef, sauerkraut, Swiss cheese, onions, garlic, horseradish and caraway; cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully scoop out potatoes, leaving shells intact.
Mash potatoes with cream cheese.
Stir into the corned beef mixture.
Mound potato mixture into the shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Return to oven for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all in bowl and put in 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 3 loaves, 9 1/4 x 6-inch.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger of ground turkey.
Cook green peppers and onions in meat.
Mix rice, soups and water in a casserole dish. Add browned hamburger.
Bake at 375° until done (rice will be tender).
Add Mozzarella cheese to top and melt.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef.
Drain fat and set aside.
Blend mayonnaise, milk, cornstarch and eggs until smooth.
Stir in meat, cheese, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Turn into pastry shell.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top and knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread-cheese casserole
directions: Crumble cornbread; mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: poulet sauce supreme(poached chicken with cream sauce)
directions: Place the chicken in a small kettle or large saucepan and add the water, bay leaf, onion with cloves, allspice, carrot, celery, salt, peppercorns and thyme. Bring to the boil and partly cover. Simmer 30 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt the butter in a large heavy saucepan and saute the onions over a low heat, stirring frequently, 20 to 30 minutes.
Increase the heat, stir and saute the onions until they are golden brown. Add the broths and simmer 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter crispy pops
directions: You will need 12 wooden sticks.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix softened margarine, powdered sugar, flour and pecans.
Mix until dough forms and put in a 14-inch pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown onion and beef.
Cook noodles until tender.
Put all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pearls 'n chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat together butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add the mixture in the small bowl.
Finally stir in the white morsels.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes, until edges are slightly browned. Let stand for 2 minutes, then remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: "beer" bread
directions: Mix
together.	Sprinkle
with	self-rising
flour
and place in	greased
loaf
pan.
Bake
at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove and spread lots of butter on top and bake for another 10 minutes.
When finished baking, butter again.

title: speedy caramel frosting
directions: Boil butter, brown sugar, salt and milk.
Blend in powdered sugar.
Add vanilla.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: wassail
directions: In a large saucepan, heat cider and cinnamon stick to boiling, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer.

title: pommes de terre en salade(hot potato salad)
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until just tender. Drain and cut into halves or quarters.
Heat oil and vinegar with salt and pepper to taste and when hot, add onion and parsley. Pour over hot potatoes and toss well.
Serve at once.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Combine 2 cups Bisquick, 2/3 cup milk and 1/2 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Use a wooden spoon to mix (about 30 seconds until soft dough ball forms).
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown at 450°.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: chocolate chip-oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, soften margarine.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; stir well.
Blend flour, soda and salt; add to sugar mixture.
Stir well.
Add oatmeal and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool.

title: gingerbread mix
directions: Combine ingredients using electric mixer.
Roll out dough to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake on lightly greased tins at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: quick and easy cherry delight pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours and serve.

title: aileen's standing rib roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
With boning knife, carve ribs from roast and save.
Rub roast generously with soy sauce and seasonings.
Place roast on top of ribs in roasting pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook for 20 minutes per pound. Transfer roast from pan to platter.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving.

title: lemon or lime pie
directions: Bake pie shells.
Cool.
Pour Eagle Brand milk in mixing bowl. Fold in lemonade or lime until thick. Add Cool Whip.
Fold.
Put in pie shells.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: no bake chocolate cheesecake
directions: In small micro-proof bowl, melt chocolate chips on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred; set aside to cool.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Melt butter in 9x13 inch pan in 300° oven.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar gradually.
Add pecan halves.
Mix until nuts are well coated with meringue.
Drop by spoonful into melted butter in pan.
Spoon some of the butter over the pecans. Bake at 300° oven for 1 hour.
Turn pecans every 15 minutes. Separate into individual nuts on the last turning.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and sour milk.
Let soak for a few minutes. Add rest of ingredients.
Bake in muffin cups at 350°.
(You can add blueberries, bananas or applesauce, but you may have to add more flour.)

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In a large pan, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and save the liquid.
In same pan, saute the onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables and 1 cup or more of reserved liquid until soup is desired consistency.
You can also add cooked beef or fried ground beef to this.
Yields 8 to 10 servings/2 1/2 quarts.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix.
When cool, crumble cake into punch bowl, dividing the amount so as to have enough for layers in your punch bowl.
Add layer of crumbs, one layer of vanilla pudding, one layer of Cool Whip and one layer of strawberry jello.
It's best to put the strawberry jello next to the cake crumbs.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Boil macaroni 8 minutes; drain.
Heat together in casserole; eggs, beaten well, milk, salt, pepper and butter.
Add drained macaroni to eggs and milk mixture.
Mix well and top with grated cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: onion bread
directions: Chop onions and cook with butter.
Put butter and onions on buns.
Put
Parmesan
cheese
on
top and bake in oven until toasted.

title: pitza biscuits
directions: Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Spread biscuits in muffin pan. Cook ground beef, barbecue sauce and onion.
Fill biscuits 2/3 full.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: shoney's potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, celery, onions, parsley and chicken bouillon in water and cook until tender.
Blend flour with small amount of milk.
Stir in vegetables.
Add remaining milk, heat but do not boil.
Add cubed cheese.
Cover and remove from heat.
Stir to blend before serving.

title: sloppy chicken
directions: Cut up 1 fryer chicken.
Roll in flour and fry until brown. Doesn't have to be tender.
Lay on paper towels to drain.
Take 2 cans cream of chicken soup and add 1 cup of milk.
Put in slow cooker (crock-pot) or in gallon cook pot.
Add chicken.
Cook on low for 2 or 3 hours.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 20 (1 1/2-inch) thick balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally until brown.
You can serve with your favorite spaghetti sauce and noodles.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat the eggs slightly, then add the sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and coconut.
Stir in the milk, slowly, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned and center is set.

title: wrap around cherry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cherries.
Wrap dough around drained maraschino cherries.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack.
Use cherry juice and powdered sugar to make icing.

title: nora's french coconut pie
directions: Mix well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: tacos(child snack recipe)
directions: Heat taco shells at 350° until crisp (3 to 5 minutes).
Brown ground beef.
Fill shell with beef; sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top with lettuce and tomato.

title: esther's satin pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Beat/whip egg whites in separate bowl. To them, add vanilla.
Add yolks to chocolate one at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and sugar.
Then add egg whites and mix well.
Pour into baked shell.
Cool/chill for an hour before serving.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine berries, sugar and pineapple in a bowl.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add marshmallows and bananas. Stir until mixed.
Combine cream and sugar.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Fold into berry mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: swiss cheese fondue sauce
directions: In large bowl, mix grated cheese and flour.
Set aside; rub inside of 3-quart saucepan with garlic and discard garlic.
Add grape juice and lemon juice; heat until liquid bubbles.
Turn heat low.
With saucepan still on low heat, gradually add cheese/flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until cheese melts.
Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Transfer to a fondue pot and serve with crusty French bread. Recipe yields 3 1/2 cups of fondue sauce.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake according to box.
Mix pudding according to box. Drain juice off of the pineapple.
In a punch bowl, start layering ingredients.
First, break up the cake.
Add some pudding, then some cherries, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Keep layering until you have four layers.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: feast day chile balls
directions: Brown the pork; add the onions and saute until onions are soft.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in the chile, raisins and sugar. Beat the egg whites until they form peaks.
Combine flour and egg yolks and mix thoroughly.
Fold the egg yolk mixture into the whites until combined to form a batter.
Take about 1 teaspoon of meat mixture, roll it in the flour and shape into 1-inch balls. Dip the chile balls into the batter and deep fry in 350° oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: marinated french dip
directions: In large shallow baking dish, combine all ingredients, except brisket and bread; add brisket.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Cover; roast at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender, turning after 45 minutes. Remove meat from baking dish; reserve cooking juices.
Cut brisket into thin slices; serve on rolls with juices for dipping. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Cut avocados in
half
lengthwise; remove pit and peel. Mash by putting avocado through a food mill or mash in a small bowl with fork.
Stir
in
remaining
ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap, placing
wrap
directly
on
surface
to prevent darkening and chill at least
hours or 3.
Serve with chips or fresh vegetables.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter with sugar; add eggs and flour, mixing well. Stir in buttermilk, nutmeg and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell; bake 45 minutes at 350° in center of oven.
Freezes well, that is if someone doesn't eat it before you can get to the freezer with it.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine ingredients in mixer; mix until smooth.
Bake in 3 layers for 25 minutes at 350°, or in long pan for 30 minutes.

title: grandma's lemon icebox pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in a small amount of hot water.
Whip cold Pet milk until thick.
Add sugar slowly.
Add Jell-O mixture and lemon juice.
Pour mixture in pie crusts.
Chill and eat.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain juice from beans and put in layers in crock or ceramic container.
Add sauce and marinate overnight in refrigerator. When ready to serve, pour off sauce.
Garnish with onion slices. Serve cold.

title: bourbon pecan cake
directions: Soak raisins in bourbon overnight. Cream butter and sugar. Gradually add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: cool fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until done, do not overcook.
Place potatoes in large bowl.
Add onion, tomato, eggs, pickles and olives to potatoes.
Add celery seed, mayonnaise and mustard.
Stir mixture only enough to mix well.
Leave potatoes diced, if possible.
Chill or serve warm.

title: crispy marshmallow bars
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, melt butter and marshmallows over low heat, stirring occasionally, until marshmallows are melted. Remove from heat; blend in vanilla.
In large bowl, add mixture to cereal; stir to coat.
Spread into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Yields 24 bars.

title: parmesan breadsticks
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, the Parmesan cheese and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, shortening, sugar and salt just until warm (115° to 120°), stirring constantly to melt shortening.
Add to dry mixture in mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Shape into a ball.
Place in lightly greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.

title: raised hush puppies
directions: Scald milk, stir in sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in 1 1/2 to 2-quart mixing bowl.
Add milk mixture, egg, onion and corn meal; stir in flour to make slightly stiff batter.
Cover with cup towel and let rise until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil; fry until golden brown, about 1 minute.

title: pepper steaks
directions: Wrap bacon slice around edges of each steak.
Coarsely grind pepper and mix with thyme and salt.
Press 1/2 teaspoon onto both sides of steaks.
Drizzle cognac over both sides of steaks.
Cover and marinate at least 2 hours (overnight is better).
Grill, panfry or boil to desired doneness but be sure to sear both sides, then lower temperature to finish cooking.

title: chinese hors d'oeuvre
directions: Cut
each
bacon
strip
into
thirds.
Wrap each water chestnut with bacon strip and secure each with toothpick.
Dip in teriyaki or soy sauce.
Arrange 12 on a dish and cover with paper towel.
Cook
in
microwave
oven
for 4 to 5 minutes on High
or until bacon is crisp.
Repeat with remaining appetizers.
Yield: 3 dozen appetizers.

title: pretzel letters
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water.
Add flour and salt and knead for 6 minutes.
Cover the dough and let it rise in a greased pan until it doubles in size.

title: robert redford
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans.
Put into 13 x 9-inch baking dish evenly.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread evenly on baked crust.
Mix milk and pudding until stiff.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top of pudding mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and drizzle 1/2 cup melted butter over that.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shoepeg corn
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese till well blended. Fold in corn and chilies. Place in 1 1/2 qt. baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tea rolls
directions: When milk is lukewarm, add yeast, then add 2 cups flour.
Beat well and let rise, then add the butter, sugar, salt and the 2 beaten eggs.
To this, add enough flour to make a soft dough. Knead well.
Let rise in a warm place, then shape into small rolls. Let rise in buttered pans.
Bake in a brisk oven at 375° for 15 minutes or more.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: sun-dried tomato pate
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in food processor or blender.
Oil a 4 to 5-cup straight sided dish and line with plastic wrap. Layer pine nuts, tomatoes, pesto and cheese mixture.
Repeat. Fold plastic wrap over top to cover.
Press gently to form.
Chill 1 hour.
Unmold, turn upside-down on plate with nuts on top. Serve with crackers.
Prepare up to 5 days ahead or freeze for 3 months.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
In large skillet, brown meat on both sides in hot shortening.
Top with onion and tomatoes.
Cover; cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Or, transfer to a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish and cook covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add green pepper; cook 15 minutes more.
Skim off excess fat.
Thicken juices, if desired.
Season to taste.
Serves 6.

title: holiday cranberry delight
directions: Cream 4 tablespoons of sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels; mix in cinnamon.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish, which has been sprayed with Pam, etc.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: dutch apple fritters
directions: Combine egg yolks, beer, oil, 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar and salt in container of blender.
Whirl on high for 1 minute.
Cover and let batter rest at room temperature for 2 hours or refrigerate overnight.
Pare and core the apples and cut into 1/2-inch thick rings.
Pour oil into a deep skillet to a 2-inch depth.
Heat oil to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into the batter.
Mix remaining flour and cinnamon in a shaker bag.
Shake rings to coat well.
Dip rings into the batter coating evenly.
Fry rings 3 to 4 minutes or until golden, browning on both sides.
Keep warm in a 250° oven.
Serve hot sprinkled with confectioners sugar and cinnamon.

title: strang beans*
directions: I pick around 6 or 7 pounds of beans in the early mornin* part of the day from my garden.
Brake* 'em* up in small peeces* about a inch long.
Worsh* real good.
Cut off the bug bites.
Cook in a big pot with enough water to cover 'em.
Put in a hunk of hog meat*.
Add a gob of lard.
Salt.
Cook til they're cooked down and the "green" is off of em*.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg and milk.
In a plastic bag, combine flour, baking powder, salt, paprika and sesame seed.
Dip chicken pieces into egg mixture, then shake one piece at a time in plastic bag.
Place skin side up in baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over and bake about one hour or until done.
Serves 5.

title: teriyaki cornish hens
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine cornstarch, brown sugar, dry mustard and ginger.
Blend in teriyaki sauce and orange juice; stir until smooth.
Cook or microwave until thickened, stirring every minute.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove giblets from hens; rinse with cold water and pat dry.
In small mixing bowl, combine rice and apricots.
Stuff hens with rice mixture; close cavities and secure.
In 3-quart oblong glass baking pan, place hens, breast side up, on trivet.
Cook at 350° for 70 minutes in convection oven or longer in regular oven.
Baste with teriyaki sauce every 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Make crumbs of first 3 ingredients. Save 1/2 cup for top of pie. Mix all ingredients together, including liquids, crumbs, etc. Fill pie pan. Put the 1/2 cup of crumbs on top. Bake at 350° less than 1 hour. Test center after 45 minutes...trial and error. Center should be "set" when done.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown beef.
Cook onion with chili and garlic until just tender.
Transfer both to Dutch oven or deep cooking pan.
Add gravy, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for 25 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add beans and cornmeal.
Stir for 5 minutes, until thickened.
Makes 14 cups.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Cook the mixture until it boils and is thickened.
Put in some celery salt and onion salt and pepper if desired.
Let cool and pour over chopped cabbage.
Makes enough for a large head of cabbage.

title: ham hot dish
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
You may put extra Cheddar cheese on top and put back in the oven for 15 minutes more.

title: mom's homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add fruit of any kind.
Freeze according to directions of ice cream maker.

title: oven baked potato salad
directions: Cube potatoes and cut up bacon; add cheese and salad dressing and mix.
Place in baking dish and pour milk over mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes.

title: beef cheese log
directions: Blend all ingredients except corned beef.
Shape into 8 or 10-inch log.
Roll in chopped corned beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: florida cheesecake
directions: Combine syrup, yogurt, eggs and gelatin in top of double boiler.
Stir constantly over medium heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Using a blender or rotary beater, blend cottage cheese with lime juice until smooth.
Combine cheese with gelatin mixture and blend well.
Fold in the whipping cream.
Pour into greased spring-form pan, which has been buttered and dusted with graham crumbs.
Chill until set.

title: chicken breast with white wine
directions: Salt and pepper chicken breasts. Place in large casserole. Mix cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and cooking wine. Pour the mixture over the chicken. Refrigerate overnight. When ready to cook, sprinkle generously with paprika. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Do not cover or turn. Serve over yellow rice.

title: strawberry-nut salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and boiling water and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread 1/2 mixture in a glass baking dish.
Chill well until set.
Spread with 1 pint of sour cream. Carefully spoon rest of strawberry mixture over top.
Chill until solid.
Serve plain or on lettuce.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Beat the egg yolk and whole egg until very light.
Beat in the water and salt.
Stir in and work the flour in with your hands. Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll out on floured board and let dry. Cut into width you prefer.

title: cumberland sauce
directions: Melt the jelly in the top of a double boiler.
Beat in all the other ingredients except the raisins and stir until the sauce is thickened.
Do not despair if this is slow work; it may take as much as 15 minutes.
I find I can read a book while I am stirring. When the sauce has thickened, stir in the raisins.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: savory meat balls
directions: Mix 1 package onion soup mix, eggs, beef and crackers in large bowl.
Make into meat balls.
Brown meat balls and drain grease. Mix 2nd package onion soup mix accordingly to package directions. Pour over meat balls and simmer covered for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Mix the blueberry pie filling and pineapple together.
Add the pecans.
Put in sheet cake pan.
Put 1/2 box of cake mix on top. Heat the butter or margarine in microwave; pour on top of cake mix.
Put in oven for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Clean outer leaves from cauliflower and wash thoroughly. Drain until completely dry.
Mix together Miracle Whip and mustard.
Spread over top of the
whole head of cauliflower.
Wrap in foil, stem side down, making sure that the foil is not touching the top of the cauliflower head.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
This is an easy, delicious alternative to the traditional steamed cauliflower.

title: cabbage wedge meal-in-one
directions: Remove tough outer leaves from cabbage and cut into 8 wedges, removing part of hard core.
Place wedges in a greased casserole. Place onions, ground beef and rice between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, hot water and seasonings and pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on high for 3 minutes.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture. Blend just until combined.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: creamed corn
directions: Put oleo in pan and melt.
Then add corn and sugar and cook on low for awhile.
Then add cream cheese, chopped.
Cook awhile longer.

title: peas and peanut slaw
directions: In salad bowl combine peas, cabbage and onions.
In a small bowl mix sour cream, mayonnaise, salt, curry, pepper, mustard and vinegar.
Blend well.
Pour over cabbage mixture and toss lightly. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour or until next day. Sprinkle peanuts over salad before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and form into balls.
Mix ketchup, vinegar, brown sugar and Worcestershire together and spoon on top of balls.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp linguine salad
directions: Boil and peel shrimp.
Cook noodles as directed and drain. Combine noodles and shrimp.
Then add green onions, tomatoes, parsley, wine vinegar, oregano, basil and garlic salt.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Mix all ingredients into yeast. Knead.
Make a ball of dough to roll and twist into any shape. Lay on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with salt.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: carob bavarian cream
directions: Soak gelatin in blender with cold water 5 minutes.
Add boiling
water
and
whiz
to
dissolve
gelatin.
Add
next 4 ingredients.
Blend until creamy smooth.
Add enough ice cubes to bring level up to 4-cup mark on blender.
Blend well.
Pour into bowl (or baked crust for pie).
Chill 3 to 4 hours, until firm.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Add rice and salt to broth.
Stir until mixture begins to boil.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend soup and milk and stir in rice, chicken, celery, onion, 1/2 c. almonds & seasonings.
Cool quickly.
Pour in casserole, sprinkle remaining 1/2 c. almonds on top.
Bake 30 - 45 minutes at 400°.

title: clam and oyster stew
directions: Put oysters, clams, shrimp, lobster meat, potatoes (cut in small bite-size) and onion in a skillet with lots of water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Take your can of milk with 1 can of water; put into pot on low.
Add all the ingredients.
Drain your skillet first.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until potatoes are done.
Serve with little crackers.
Um-um good.

title: mother's pecan rolls
directions: Melt bits over hot water.
Mix with condensed milk.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Make into 2 rolls and cover with pecan halves. Roll in wax paper, then foil.
Chill.
Cut in slices to serve.

title: strawberry champagne punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
In a "Punch Bowl" combine gelatin mixture, lemonade and cold water.
Test before serving.
Stir in wine, champagne and strawberries.
24 1/2 cup serving.

title: pepper steak
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Cut round steak into bite-size. Mix with bouillon cubes, Worcestershire sauce to taste and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Add water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar.
Mix in onion and pepper.
Let simmer until ready to serve over rice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Layer sausage in casserole and top with bread.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over sausage and bread.
Top with cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all and bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: string beans and tomatoes
directions: Thoroughly cook sliced sausage and onion in skillet.
Place string beans and stewed tomatoes in pot.
Add sausage and onion mixture into string beans.
Season with salt, pepper and Creole seasoning as desired.
Cook on low heat 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf(stove top)
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients; let simmer while making meat loaf.
Mix all remaining ingredients together.
Add enough bread crumbs to hold meat together.
Cook in sauce on medium-low heat for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
The sauce may be used as a gravy for potatoes.

title: homemade horseradish
directions: In blender, pour vinegar.
Scrape horseradish root.
Do not peel.
Cut up in 1/2-inch pieces.
Drop in blender with vinegar. Blend slowly to a thickness of applesauce.
Freeze if you like.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Add pecans; beat well.
Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans. Fill 1/2 full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After cooled, put lids on cans.

title: fudge
directions: Gradually add sugar to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional nuts, if desired.
Yields 1 3/4 pounds.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain the cans of beans.
Thoroughly wash the juice off the kidney beans.

title: chicken marbella
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken quarters, garlic, oregano, pepper and salt to taste, vinegar, olive oil, dried fruit, olives, capers and juice and bay leaves.
Cover and let marinate, refrigerated, overnight.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add beef, onion and pepper; brown very slightly.
Add salt to taste.
Add soup and simmer for 10 minutes; stir in sour cream and pimento.
Place in a baking dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: quick and easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Mix next five ingredients and pour over margarine.
Pour undrained peaches over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You can also use other types of fruits.

title: beet and celery salad mold
directions: Mix water with jello.
After cooling add beet juice; set until it begins to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drain 3 teaspoons horseradish and stir into mayonnaise.
Add to mixture and pour into mold.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box instructions. When cake is cool, tear apart and crumble into large bowl or container.
Pour pineapple and juice over the cake.
Prepare vanilla pudding according to box instructions and put this mix over the pineapple. Pour cherry pie filling over all this using a spoon.
Make occasional holes so mixture can seep to the bottom of the bowl. Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts, if desired. Refrigerate.

title: banana pancakes(yield: 4 servings)
directions: 1. Mash banana(s) in mixing bowl.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken; debone and skin. Cut into bite-size pieces. Place in large casserole dish. Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken. Melt butter and crumble crackers. Mix and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with poppy seed and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Mix butter, sugar and boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add to the butter and sugar mixture which has cooled to lukewarm.
Beat eggs.
Add to mixture.
Add 4 cups of flour and beat with mixer on low speed until blended.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and salt; stir this in.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or up to 2 days.
Divide into two parts; roll out and brush with butter flavored Crisco, then sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll into jelly roll and slice.
Place in a greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° to 400° for approximately 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar glaze.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with 1/2 of the cracker crumbs.
Separate the eggs.
Beat the egg yolks, powdered sugar and melted butter until light colored.
In another bowl, beat the egg whites until very stiff.
Fold the beaten egg whites gently into the egg yolk mixture.
Spread over the crackers.
Sprinkle the drained pineapple over this.
Beat the whipped cream until it starts to thicken.
Gradually beat in the sugar.
Stir in the vanilla.
Pour and spread whipped cream over the pineapple layer. Cover with the rest of the graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze.
Serve as a cool, frozen summer treat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Place macaroni in 3-quarts of boiling water with 1 teaspoon salt.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Drain macaroni and add the chopped or diced green peppers, celery, onions and tomatoes in medium bowl. Mix French dressing and Miracle Whip together and pour over salad.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt
butter
in
9 x 13-inch dish.
Add graham cracker crumbs,
chocolate
chips,
coconut, butterscotch chips, Eagle Brand milk
and pecans in order.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool in pan and cut into bars.

title: barbecue spice
directions: Mix together and use as seasoned salt.
Great for anyone on a salt restricted diet.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat undrained pineapple until boiling.
Add Jell-O and dissolve.
Cool; add buttermilk.
Let this mixture cool and fold in Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly and congeal.

title: apricot bread
directions: Cover apricots in warm water and soak 30 minutes.
Drain and cut with scissors.
Cream sugar and butter; add egg.
Add water and juice.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to other sugar-egg mixture.
Blend in nuts and apricots.

title: cowboy stew
directions: In Dutch oven cook and brown ground meat.
Add onions and stir and cook well.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add all other ingredients and simmer until hot.
This stew can be cooked over an open campfire.

title: meringue angel pie
directions: Whip egg whites with cream of tartar and pinch of salt until frothy.
Slowly beat in the sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until meringue is stiff and glossy.
Spread meringue into a well-buttered and floured 9-inch pie plate but reserve some for piping around edges.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes, or until meringue is dry and crisp, and top is slightly browned.

title: baked carrot squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray Pam on an 8-inch pan.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and Equal. in a separate bowl, dissolve soda in Butter Buds and add to dry ingredients.
Stir in egg.
Add carrots and raisins.
Mix and pour into pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: italian biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour pan well.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, stir and cook meat, onions and green bell pepper until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Heat through; pour into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover; bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Stir in corn meal.
Add milk to beaten egg and stir into first mixture. Add oleo and blend.
Turn into greased 8-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: speidini
directions: On cutting board, pound steaks into 4 x 8-inch oval.
Lay on top of that 1 slice of thin ham that just reaches the edge of the steak.
Lay on spinach the same, one good size chopped mushroom on top of that, 2 tablespoons of diced tomatoes, 3 heaping tablespoonfuls of cheese and sprinkle with a pinch of basil, garlic and oregano.
Roll all of this together, making sure to keep all the stuffing inside.
When through rolling, it should be tubular shaped, 4
inches or so wide.
Dust with oil, roll in spiced bread crumbs and grill for about 15 minutes.
Also can be baked at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Best served with sauteed mushrooms, garlic and white wine.

title: french pork chops
directions: Lay pork chops in baking pan.
Sprinkle on salt, pepper and onion soup mix.
Pour on French dressing and add enough water to cover the meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: best pie crust
directions: Cut together flour, Crisco and salt with pastry blender.
Mix well cold water and flour and add to first mixture.
Stir with fork, then squeeze with hands.
Roll out on floured surface. Makes 2 single or 1 double crust.
To bake before filling, bake at 400° until golden.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Put chicken on flat pan; dab with butter.
(I brush mine with oil.)
Put in oven at 400° until browned slightly.
Then cover with sauce.
Reduce temperature to 325°.
Cook 1 hour or until chicken is tender and sauce thickens.
Sauce is also good for ribs.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all together; stir until candy melts over hot burner. Bring to a boil then simmer one hour.
Serve hot.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together and pack in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Remove crab meat from shells; wash shells carefully.
Combine crab meat, bread, butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Moisten with milk, into which a dash of Tabasco sauce has been stirred; mixture should be rather soft.
Pack loosely into crab shells; top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven until delicately browned.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: wyatt's eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and cube eggplant; boil 30 minutes.
Saute vegetables in margarine until tender.
Add to crumb and milk mixture.
To drained eggplant, add remaining ingredients, except cheese.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Combine beans, broth, garlic and half of onions in a large soup pot.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer at least 2 hours, until beans are soft, adding more broth or water, if necessary.
In a skillet, saute remaining onion in oil until tender.
Add chilies and seasonings and mix thoroughly.
Add to bean mixture.
Add chicken and simmer one hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese, salsa and sour cream.

title: 125 year-old black walnut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease tube pan.
Cream together butter and shortening; mix in sugar well.
Add one egg at a time.
Add flavorings.
Mix in flour, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add milk and nuts.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: After 60 days (required to cut elephant into enough small cubes), place elephant in a 5-ton casserole.
Add enough brown gravy to cover and cook in a 325° oven for 4 weeks.
Cook Creamettes as directed on the package.
Drain; do not chill.
Mix immediately with elephant.
Serve hot.
Makes 3,752 servings. Should your guests bring their guests, add 2 rabbits, but only it necessary because most people don't like to discover hare in their stew.

title: crock-pot beef stroganoff
directions: Mix meat and soups together in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Add sour cream and mushrooms and cook for another 30 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: cherry pecan bread
