directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt; set aside.
In another bowl, combine eggs, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until combined. Fold in nuts and cherries.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter in a medium bowl.
Add sugar, beating well.
Combine flour and cinnamon; add to creamed mixture, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Press dough from a cookie press into 2-inch strips onto ungreased cookie sheets, following manufacturer's instructions.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Remove from cookie sheets and cool completely on wire racks.
Yield: 9 dozen (24 calories each).

title: scrumptious skillet cookies
directions: Heat eggs, dates and sugar in skillet over low heat, until it stays together.
Remove from heat and add all other ingredients, except coconut.
Cool.
Roll into balls, roll balls in coconut.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from the table.
Grease pan; crack nuts.
Measure two cups flour; remove baby's hands from flour.
Wash flour off baby; re-measure.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter. Get dust pan and brush up pieces of bowl baby knocked on the floor.
Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.
Return to kitchen. Remove baby's hands from bowl; wash baby and answer phone. Return; remove 1/4 inch salt from greased pan.
Look for baby. Grease another pan.
Answer telephone.
Return to kitchen and find baby; remove his hands from the bowl.
Take up greased pan and find layer of nutshells in it.
Head for baby who flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash kitchen floor, table, walls, dishes.
Call baker.
Lie down.

title: oven stew
directions: Melt the margarine in a skillet.
Add the celery, green peppers, garlic and onions.
Saute until softened and slightly browned.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Dust with the flour and seasonings.
Add to the skillet; saute until browned.
Stir in the sugar, salt, tomato, mushrooms, broth and wine.
Transfer to a buttered 3-quart casserole.
Cover.
Let stand several hours. Bake at 350° for 2 hours (uncovered).
Stir in olives 5 minutes before done.
Note:
Start early afternoon.

title: brown bag caramel corn
directions: You will need 1 large brown grocery bag.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Brown ground beef and after it's cooked, pour in the tomato sauce; stir together.
When noodles are done, drain and rinse in cool water.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pour a small amount of sauce in the bottom before putting noodles in, keeps from sticking.
Put one layer of noodles, then put some cheese.
Continue layering until noodles are gone or until you have reached the top of the pan.
Allow yourself 1 to 1 1/2-inches from top.
On the last layer or top layer, pour the remaining sauce over noodles; sprinkle last of the cheese (I like to have a lot of cheese on top).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, sugar, egg yolks and milk and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, and butter; stir and pour into a baked pie shell.

title: triple fudge brownies
directions: Prepare pudding according to pkg. directions.
Whisk in cake mix.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-35 minutes or until the top springs back when lightly touched.
Dust with confectioners' sugar.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix shrimp with softened cream cheese.
Add vegetables.
Add remaining ingredients.
Use enough dressing to achieve desired consistency for spreading.
May be used for fingertip sandwiches or as spread for crackers.

title: chicken or ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Saute onions in butter, set aside.
In same skillet, brown ground beef.
Then mix meat with onions and cottage cheese.
In greased casserole, arrange 1/3 noodles, then 1/2 meat mixture.
Repeat.
Place remaining noodles on top. Combine stock, soup and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Pour beaten eggs over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 375°.

title: wasehi
directions: Lightly brown meats; drain fat and set aside.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix all other ingredients together with meat and noodles. Place in an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: sugar and spice glazed pecans
directions: You will need 1 large Ziploc bag or large resealable container.

title: cranberry fruit nut bread
directions: Measure flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and orange peel in bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough water to orange juice to make 3/4 cup.
Add juice and egg into flour mixture. Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into loaf pan 9 x 5 x 3-inches, which has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Wrap while warm and slice the next day.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let set for 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube or Bundt pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust.
Bake until pie is set.
Insert knife near center.
It will come out clean if pie is done.

title: marshmallow fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth and creamy. Add crushed pineapple; blend well.
Stir in fruit cocktail and chopped cherries.
Add package of marshmallows;
fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes a large bowl.

title: fried cheese meltaways
directions: Heat 2 inches of oil in deep fat fryer to 375°.
Beat 1 cup of baking mix, milk and egg with hand beater until smooth.
Coat cheese lightly with baking mix.
Insert a round wooden toothpick in each cube.
Dip into batter, covering cheese completely.
Fry several cubes at a time, turning carefully until golden brown,
1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
(Leave toothpicks in.
Keep oil moving with basket or slotted spoon.)

title: pickled corn
directions: Cook corn on-the-cob until done.
Let cool and cut corn off. Fill jars to 1/2 inch from top.
Add 1 tablespoon of pickling salt and 1 teaspoon of vinegar.
Fill jars with real hot water and seal. Store in a cool place.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten eggs.
Beat until mixture is very stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.
Put in ice cream freezer and freeze.
This recipe will serve 8 people.

title: microwave easy onion soup
directions: Cut each onion in half from stem to root end, then slice thinly crosswise.
In 3-quart casserole, cook onions and butter on High 15 minutes, stirring twice.
Add undiluted beef broth and 1 cup of water.
Cook, covered, on High 10 minutes, stirring once.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt, soda, sugar and cinnamon.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans. Spoon batter into 2 greased loaf pans and bake 1 hour at 350°. Let stand overnight before slicing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and drop on cookie sheet, teaspoon size.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Place in microwave-safe dish, preferably tube-style.
Cook on High 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix pumpkin, water, oil and eggs together.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into muffin tins sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 16 to 18 muffins.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is still hot, punch holes in the cake, using a fork.
Pour milk and cream of coconut on top of cake.
Let cake cool, then spread Cool Whip and top with frozen coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: texas pralines
directions: Cook sugars, milk, syrup and salt to soft ball stage (236°). Remove from heat.
Add butter and flavoring.
Stir until syrup begins to thicken.
Add broken pecans and drop from a spoon into cakes on waxed paper placed on a cookie sheet.
Press pecan halves into surface, working quickly because pralines harden rapidly!

title: 7 minute icing
directions: Mix all ingredients in top of double boiler, place over boiling water and cook for 7 minutes, beating constantly with an electric mixer until it will hold a peak.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and mix until it is the right consistency to spread on cake.

title: hot milk cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until thick, about 5 minutes. Gradually add sugar, beating until mixture is light and fluffy. Combine flour and baking powder; add to batter with vanilla and beat at low speed until smooth.
In a saucepan, heat milk and butter just until the butter melts.
Add to batter, beating until combined.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Electric Mixer:
Cream the 2 sugars, margarine and oil.
Add beaten egg, milk and oil; mix well.
Combine flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Add this to creamy mixture and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts (optional).
Use tablespoon to spoon on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: scallop corn
directions: Beat eggs and cracker crumbs.
Add milk, salt, pepper, sugar, creamed corn and butter.
Mix well.
Dot the top of the mixture with butter and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pita pizza bites
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Split each bread in half around edge with knife to make 4 rounds.
Place rounds, cut sides up, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Place mushrooms on bread rounds.
Top with onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle with basil and cheese.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Cut each round into 8 pieces.

title: wonder pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut stew
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening until tender.
Add all remaining ingredients except frankfurters.
Simmer, covered, 35 minutes or until ingredients are tender.
Add frankfurters; simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill thoroughly.
Have vegetables ready for dipping.

title: fattening cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a full rolling boil for about 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by spoon on wax paper.
Cool until firm.

title: artichoke dip(easy and delicious)
directions: Mix together.
Place in oven to tableware.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no name chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Melt butter in skillet. Stir in dressing.
Place cut up chicken in mixture and cook chicken until tender.
Mix in soup, cream cheese and wine.
Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Can be served over rice or noodles.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in small amount of butter until tender, not brown. Add meat and first seasonings.
Brown lightly.
Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mash potatoes while hot.
Add milk, egg, salt and pepper.
Drop in mounds over the meat.
If desired, sprinkle potatoes with shredded cheese.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into shallow Pyrex dish and refrigerate overnight.

title: no sugar pink salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat with mixer.
Fold in cottage cheese, Cool Whip and fruit.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: lima broccoli casserole
directions: Pour melted oleo or butter over the top of all ingredients. Bake for 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: damn good chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic salt. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Cook, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, sour cream, vanilla and oil together until well blended.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 13 x 9-inch or tube pan.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Sprinkle half over mixture. Swirl with knife.
Pour other half of mixture into pan and sprinkle remaining brown sugar mixture; swirl.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine red wine vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed, stir to dissolve and bring to a boil.
Chill liquid mixture and pour over sliced cucumbers, onions and green peppers.
(Peppers are optional.)

title: guacamole
directions: Cut avocados in half, remove seed and scoop out flesh.
Add a little lemon juice to maintain color (I use a few sprinkles, maybe a Tbsp.) Mash avocados with about a 1/2 C. mayonnaise (enough to make dip consistency)
Add other ingredients.
Mix together and serve with chips.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa, then add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Combine onion, tomatoes and green beans in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add bouillon and spices. Cover, reduce heat and simmer approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef noodle soup
directions: In a Dutch oven or soup kettle, brown beef and onion; drain. Add tomatoes, broth, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a boil; add noodles.
Reduce heat to medium-low; cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until the noodles are done.
Yields 6 to 8 servings. Makes 2 quarts.

title: waldorf hotel red cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add food coloring and cocoa. Sift flour and salt. Mix all with buttermilk, vanilla and baking soda mixed with vinegar.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Split layers and frost with butter frosting with almond flavoring added.

title: chicken wingettes
directions: Lay wings in pan.
Pour oil on top of wings.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic powder, basil and parsley evenly on both sides.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour, basting occasionally, then add water to bottom of pan and cover with foil for another 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Squeeze fresh lemon over top of wings. Let sit for 5 minutes.

title: atlantic pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops in hot oil at 375°.
Remove chops; add celery and cook lightly.
Drain fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients; add chops.
Bring to boil.
Simmer covered for 30 minutes.

title: cavatelli
directions: Cook noodles while browning meat.
Drain.
Add onion, mushrooms and Ragu and taco sauces.
Simmer. Drain noodles.
Lay noodles on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer meat mixture on noodles. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken-sausage cassoulet
directions: In saucepan, combine carrots, onion and water.
Simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Transfer to crock-pot.
Stir in tomato paste, wine and seasonings.
Add beans.
Place frozen chicken and sausage atop beans.
Cover; cook on low for 9 to 10 hours or on high for 5 1/2 to 6 hours.

title: festive holiday salad
directions: Mix together in large bowl, broccoli, artichokes, green onions, black olives, cooked macaroni and mushrooms.
Mix all together.
Pour salad dressing over mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Add tomato and avocado before serving.

title: oven "fried" chicken
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put butter and oil in 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt in oven.
Remove pan from oven as soon as mixture is melted. Combine bread crumbs, flour and spices.
Put in a Ziploc bag.
Put chicken pieces in oil and butter mixture.
Shake off excess fat. Then put each piece in bag of flour mixture and shake until coated. Place chicken in pan and cook.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until chicken is browned, crispy and fully cooked.

title: taco casserole
directions: Be careful in your selection. Do not choose too young, and only such varieties as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
When once decided upon and selected, let that fact remain proven, settled and give your entire thought to preparation for domestic use.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others are constantly getting them into hot water.

Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses; keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grind granola in food processor for 2 minutes; set aside.

title: orange sugared scones
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
In small bowl combine 1/2 cup sugar, currants and orange peel.
Stir into flour mixture.

title: spinach elegante
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package.
Drain well. Spread on bottom of 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and mushrooms.
Sprinkle with dash of pepper and marjoram. Bake for 15 minutes in a 325° oven.
Remove casserole from oven and cover with sour cream and cheese. Return to oven for about 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Mix sausage, dip and buttermilk.
To the sausage mixture, add the meal and flour.
Mix well.
Grease small muffin tins well and fill with mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fiesta fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, milk and salt in heavy 3-quart saucepan; bring to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted. Add marshmallows and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Fold in candies; immediately spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and cheese.
Place in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with chips and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: benedictine sandwich spread
directions: Mash cream cheese with cucumber pulp.
Add onion, salt and enough mayonnaise to make a smooth spread.
Add small amount of green food coloring to make a very pale green.

title: mom's goulash
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, layer 1/2 of potatoes, 1/2 of onions, all hamburger, 1/2 cheese.
Then the other half of potatoes, onions and top with remaining cheese.
Salt and pepper and cover with milk.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Follow directions for baking on cake mix. Use a Bundt cake pan.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Cook sausage over medium heat until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well and reserve drippings.
Add butter to drippings to measure 1/4 cup.
Set sausage and drippings aside.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, milk and 1/4 cup reserved drippings; stir well.
Add liquid mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in cheese and sausage.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pan, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove muffins from pan immediately.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: monterey casserole
directions: Cook beef in skillet for 5 minutes or until done.
Add onion, salt and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
If adding chili powder, do so now.
Place about 3 cups chips in casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Pour meat sauce over that and top with remaining chips and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all and bake at 250° for 10 minutes.
Stir and bake another 10 minutes.

title: banana-raspberry bread("brendan's favorite")
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.

title: reception salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use juice and water for making jello.
Set aside to cool.
Mash pimentos and cream cheese together.
Add celery, pecans, pineapple and whipped cream.
Add to cooled jello.
Pour into large 9 x 13-inch dish and chill 2 hours. Serves 12.

title: rainbow float
directions: Fill a tall glass half way with red fruit punch drink or fruit juice.
Scoop about 2/3 of a cup of lemon sherbet into the glass. Fill the glass with lemon-lime carbonated beverage or sparkling water.
Then serve right away.
Makes 1 float.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine and put into greased baking dish.

title: carrot cutlets
directions: Combine the carrots, onions, rice, one egg and white sauce. Season.
Shape into cakes.
Dip into crumbs, egg and crumbs again. Fry until delicately browned on both sides.

title: shirley's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugars and eggs.
Mix all the dry ingredients together; mix well.
Chill in refrigerator.
Roll dough into balls.
Place them on an ungreased cookie sheet.
To coat with sugar use two glass pans:
Put sugar in one and spray the bottom of the other with Pam cooking spray.
Dip in the sugar and mash balls flat;
do this twice.
Bake at 325° until outside edge turns golden brown.

title: taffy
directions: Add sugar,
syrup
and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Cook until it spins a thread and then add butter and vanilla.
Pour into cupcake pans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers.
Put crumbled potato chips or crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.
Spoon 1 cup mixture into a 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of wafers and bananas.
Repeat layering, ending with pudding.
Chill.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut into small pieces with scissors. Drop in pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar over biscuits. Bake.

title: hot fudge pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa in a bowl.
Add beaten eggs, butter and vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After this has cooled and is cut to serve, warm in microwave a few seconds.

title: my favorite banana bread(heals family recipes)
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream the first 2 ingredients.
Add the eggs and banana. Mix well. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the buttermilk, mixing well after each addition. Fold in the walnuts.

Pour into greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch bread pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean. Cool loaf completely on wire rack. Wrap loaf in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Line casserole in layers with asparagus, soup and cheese. Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: butter pan fried chicken
directions: Season chicken with garlic on one side, seasoning salt on the other.
Sprinkle one side with liquid hickory and sprinkle both sides with parsley.
Let set for 30 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Dip washed chicken into the melted butter.
Combine cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Coat chicken with the seasoning mixture.
Place in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Do not cover.

title: a fine toasted coconut cake
directions: Mix at medium speed pudding, white cake mix, water, butter or margarine and eggs.
Pour batter into greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until done. Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Heat this in a saucepan and simmer about 5 minutes.
Add 4 to 5 cups of slivered beef roast or pot roast.
Heat through well and serve on hamburger or onion buns.
Can make ahead and reheat.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: sour cream pecan cake
directions: In small bowl, mix first three ingredients with electric mixer.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup; level off.
In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa and baking soda; blend well.
In large bowl, beat 1 cup sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture; blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup of the pecans.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together first 6 ingredients plus juice.
Stir in oranges.
Pour into a greased 9x9-inch pan.
Bake for 35-40 minutes.

title: granny cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, pineapple (and juice), eggs, soda and salt. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool 10 minutes and pour on icing.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison into 1/4-inch strips and marinate 4 to 6 hours in refrigerator.
Remove venison from refrigerator and blot or drip dry.
Add black pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Pound into venison with steak hammer.
Brush on liquid smoke and cover with paper towel.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Meat will continue to cook after microwave shuts off.

title: cracker snackers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl. Add crackers, tossing well. Drizzle oil over crackers; stir well. Place mixture in a large paper bag; fold bag to close and let stand 2 hours, shaking bag occasionally. Store in an airtight container. These are excellent!!

title: oriental stir-fry
directions: Slice carrots diagonally.
Mix and marinate prime steak in its gravy with seasonings down to cornstarch.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours. Saute onions, then add all vegetables except pea pods.
Cook to al dente.
Remove and saute prime steak with a small amount of marinade.
Add more marinade then cornstarch that has been mixed with a little water.
Allow to thicken and coat prime steak.
Add vegetables and mix carefully.
Only heat, keeping vegetables al dente.
Toss in fresh pea pods and cashews.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix chocolate and water.
Add butter, eggs, alternate flour and milk.
Add sugar, vanilla, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with any icing.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Slice carrots into dime-size slices.
Boil in salted water 15 minutes; drain.
Place carrots in dish and top with onion rings and green pepper rings.
Pour hot mixture* over all.
Serve hot or cold.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pineapple over that.
Sprinkle cake mix (direct from box) over fruit.
Then add nuts.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook chuck roast for 8 hours on high in crock-pot.
Remove fat and bones, then shred.
Add seasonings; cook 1 more hour.
Serve on sub buns with cheese, sauteed mushrooms, onions and green peppers.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: crusty top sour cream pound cake
directions: Sift flour with soda twice.
Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar slowly, beating constantly to cream well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each.
Stir in sour cream.
Add flour mixture, 1/2 cup at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured tube pan (I use Baker's Joy spray). Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Can use lemon extract instead of vanilla.)
Serve plain or with favorite topping with Cool Whip.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Put it in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Salt and pepper to taste.
Slice onion into rings and sprinkle on top of meat.
Slice carrot and put on top of onion.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 can water.
Spread mushroom soup over carrots.
Line Tater Tots on top.
Bake,
uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Bone and skin chicken, if necessary.
Cut into 1-inch cubes. Toss with curry, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Refrigerate until cold.
Then combine cantaloupe, grapes, nuts, ginger, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.
Great for luncheon!

title: sombrero appetizer
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add cheese and Miracle Whip and stir.
Put in casserole dish and bake 10 minutes at 350°, stirring after 5 minutes.
Sprinkle tomatoes and olives over top. Serve warm with crackers.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in molasses, flour and dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Roll balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Roll balls in sugar; place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes at 350°.

title: "play" dough
directions: Mix well.
Knead until smooth.
This dough may be kept in a plastic bag or covered container and used again.
If it gets sticky, more flour may be added.

title: shredded chicken sandwiches
directions: Cook down chickens.
Take chicken off bone and shred.
Add soup, toast and chicken broth to chicken to make consistency of sandwiches.

title: red cake
directions: Mix vinegar and soda together and set aside.
Mix together all remaining ingredients and add vinegar and soda.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) cake pans (greased and floured) for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked italian macaroni
directions: Place Ricotta in large bowl.
Add egg yolk; mix.
Add Mozzarella, Parmesan, nutmeg and basil; mix well.
Add 1 1/2 cups meat sauce; combine well.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix onions, peppers, mushrooms, soups, chili powder and milk in large bowl.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, crush Doritos and place them in single layer on the bottom of pan.
Place chicken in single layer on top of Doritos.
Cover chicken with mixture in bowl.
Cover mixture with cheese and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coral salad
directions: Soften gelatine in 1/2 cup water.
Heat tomato soup, no water added.
Add softened gelatine to this.
Work in 2 packages cream cheese; beat well with egg beater.
Cool, then add mayonnaise, celery and green pepper.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
In another bowl, sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
In another bowl, mix buttermilk, vanilla and coloring together.
Add the dry ingredients and the liquid ingredients alternately with the sugar mixture.
When well blended, fold in baking soda dissolved in vinegar.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes for 2 (8-inch) round pans or 45 minutes for 1 (9 x 13-inch) oblong cake at 350°.
Cool and frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: apple chehalis
directions: Stir together 1 beaten egg, 3/4 cup sugar, flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold in apple and nutmeats.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and 1/8 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed together.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: skyline dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Spread onion evenly over top.
Heat (prepare) chili according to directions and then pour over cream cheese. Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over Skyline.
Heat approximately 2 minutes in microwave.
Serve with chips for dipping.

title: cornflake candy
directions: Mix Karo and sugar in saucepan until melted.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Put cornflakes into a buttered pan. Pour melted mixture over cornflakes.
Cool and cut into squares. Enjoy!

title: peaches and cream
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange a large can sliced peaches (save some juice) on top of cake mix.

title: chinese tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine tuna with noodles, celery, onion, green pepper and cashews.
Stir together soup and water; pour over tuna mixture.
Stir slightly.
Place in 3-quart casserole; sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cornbread-pecan dressing
directions: Prepare cornbread and cool.
Dice liver and saute in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add celery and onion.
Saute 5 minutes longer. Crumble cornbread in large bowl and add mixture along with the other seasonings.
Stir in pecans and broth.
If cooked separately, place in well buttered 3-quart casserole and bake for 30 minutes, covered, at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer. Makes 9 to 10 cups of dressing.

title: 'simmon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat egg slightly and melt butter.
Blend into the persimmon pulp and mix thoroughly.
Pour into well greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, cheese, kidney beans, onion and chopped peppers.
In a small bowl, mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayonnaise, blending well.
Pour over chicken mixture, stirring well.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with chopped tomatoes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: spicy chocolate crackle-top cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients. In a large bowl, beat margarine, brown sugar, yogurt, egg whites and vanilla with electric mixer until blended (mixture will look curdled). Gradually beat in flour mixture until blended. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours until firm enough to handle.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Melt the margarine in a pan on top of stove.
Set aside.
In mixing bowl, crumble brown sugar and beat in melted margarine. Add eggs, one at a time and beat mixture after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this gradually to sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips.
Mix again. Spread into a greased 9 1/2 x 13 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in large bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl and add pudding mixture. Beat until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick). Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and walnuts.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon and add to mixture.
Add milk.
Coat berries with 2 teaspoons flour and fold into batter.
Cook in greased and floured tubed pan. Cook 70 to 80 minutes at 350° (preheated).

title: 5 flavors pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour, milk and flavorings.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add eggs and sour cream; mix well.
Add 1 can creamed corn and 1 can whole kernel corn (saving liquid).
Add water to liquid to equal 2/3 can.
Mix well.
Add package Jiffy mix and mix well.
Bake at 350° until brown and puffy, about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until meat falls off bones.
Drain.
Reserve broth.
Cook noodles in half the broth.
Blend flour into remaining broth to make gravy.
Add salt and pepper and soup to gravy.
Layer chicken, noodles and gravy in 2-quart casserole. Top with pimiento.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: praline cookies
directions: Arrange crackers on a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cookie sheet. Combine butter and sugar in a saucepan; heat to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Boil 2 minutes more.
Stir in pecans and spoon over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cut while still warm.
Cut each cracker in half or smaller.
Spread on foil paper.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
Put 1 cup Pepperidge Farm dressing in pan.
Put 1/2 can of salmon on crumbs.
Add 1 package of grated cheese.
Repeat.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, add butter, shortening, confectioners sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla. Mix thoroughly with a wooden spoon.
Blend in flour and salt gradually.
Divide dough in half.
Keep half in large bowl, put other half in another mixing bowl.
Add red food coloring to one half.
Shape one teaspoon of dough (each color) into a 4-inch rope.
For smooth, even ropes roll back and forth on floured board.
Place ropes side by side, lightly press together and twist.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Curve top down to form handle of cane.
Bake about 9 minutes until set.
Very light brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add rest of ingredients. Serves 12.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in the blender.
Use as a dip with vegetables or as a salad dressing.
Veggies that are good with this:
carrots, celery, turnips, jicamas, green pepper, cauliflower.

title: apple cottage pudding
directions: Peel and slice 4 to 6 medium apples and cook for 10 minutes. Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.
Pour over this batter made with: 1/2 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons sugar, milk, salt, flour and baking powder.
Bake in 375° oven, about 35 minutes.

title: coq au vin(chicken with wine sauce)
directions: Brown chicken in oil and remove from pan.
Brown carrots, onions and garlic until onions are soft and carrots are crisp-tender.
Stir in 1 cup wine and 1 cup water.
Stir in flour/parsley mixture until smooth.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Replace chicken and simmer about 45 minutes to an hour.
If using fresh mushrooms, add during last 1/2 hour of cooking.
If using canned mushrooms, add during last 15 minutes.
Just before serving, add last 1/2 cup wine and turn up heat to boil.
Serve over white rice.
This recipe is easily doubled or tripled.

title: fail-proof meringue
directions: First, dissolve 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 2 tablespoons cold water in small saucepan.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat; let cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well after each.
Add salt, vanilla and cornstarch mixture.
Spread over pie, being sure to seal the edge.
Bake at about 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: peach tart(deliciously different)
directions: In a bowl, combine cake flour, whole-wheat flour, 2 tablespoons sugar and salt. Cut in the butter until crumbly. Add oil and toss with a fork. Gradually add water and buttermilk. Toss until mixture sticks together; shape into a ball, cover and put in refrigerator for at least an hour to chill. Then roll out dough on a lightly floured surface to a 14-inch circle. Place on a parchment-lined or lightly greased baking sheet. (I use pizza pan.)

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Measure out Special K in
a large bowl. Set aside.
Bring syrup and sugar to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter. Mix well.
Pour over cereal.
Drop on wax paper in clusters.

title: turkey steaks with mushrooms
directions: Melt butter in skillet on medium-high.
When butter begins to brown, add turkey.
Cook 3 minutes; turn.
Reduce heat to medium. Add mushrooms and onions.
Cover.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove turkey to platter.
Combine bouillon and 1/4 cup water; add to skillet. Stir and heat 1 minute.
Pour over turkey.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fig preserves
directions: Place peeled figs in saucepan and sprinkle with jello and sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand for 45 minutes.
Start cooking on low heat for 5 minutes.
Then boil for 15 minutes.
Freeze in airtight containers.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until creamy, or stir until creamy.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips (and pecan pieces).
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
*If nuts are omitted, use 1 1/2 cups chips.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash,
slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise,
sugar
and well beaten eggs together.
Add squash
to this
mixture.
Pour
squash mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle finely crushed Ritz cracker crumbs
over the
squash mixture and drizzle a little squeeze Parkay
butter over crumbs, then grated cheese.
Repeat layer of
squash, cracker crumbs and cheese again.
Sprinkle sliced almonds on top. Cook at 350° for about 25 minutes until set.

title: easy fudge topped yummy dessert
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk.
Let thicken, then fold in thawed Cool Whip.
Spread a layer of graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with half the pudding mixture.
Spread another layer of graham crackers.
Top with remaining pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Microwave about two-thirds of an 18-ounce jar of hot fudge sauce until soft and spoon and spread over the top layer of graham crackers.
Chill until firm.
Yummmmm.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water; when cooled, add cranberry juice, lemon juice and orange juice.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Freeze a couple trays of the juice to be used in punch bowl when ready for serving.

title: jo's favorite company chicken
directions: Crush garlic clove into butter as it is melting.
Add salt. Dip washed and dried chicken into melted butter, then into crumb mixture.
Bake in shallow pan or dish, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes or until it tests done. Serves 10 elegantly!

title: apple pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together.
Fill pie shell with apples and spread flour and sugar mixture over the top.
Cut butter into thin slices and put on top before putting top pie shell over the top.
Sprinkle top crust with sugar.
Bake at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in a greased muffin pan at 425° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: youth camp ham roll-ups
directions: Lay cheese slice on one piece of ham.
Top with broccoli spear.
Roll cheese, broccoli and ham into a bundle and place "seam" side down in a shallow baking pan.
Heat at 350° just until ham is heated and cheese begins to melt.
So easy and so good!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: lynda's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes and onion together (chopped and peeled).
Cool. Fry bacon extra crispy and break up into bits.
Combine potatoes, onion, bacon, relish, salad dressing, celery seed and red pepper. Ready to serve.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Chill several hours before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix well and pour over 2 chickens, cut up.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste once during cooking. Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and oil.
Gradually add sugars, beating at medium speed with mixer.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar; gradually add this to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, rice cereal, chocolate chips and nuts (if desired).
If possible, refrigerate dough to cool before cooking (if you can wait that long).
Drop dough by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (don't wait until the cookies are brown).
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: old-time raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine with brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
To molasses add soda and combine with first mixture.
Add flour; stir in raisins and walnut pieces.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: kiddie chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Chex.
Pat into pan.
When hardened, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour into butter.
Add drained peaches.
Sprinkle top with small amount sugar.
Bake at 350° until brown.
May use blackberries, apples, strawberries, etc.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Beat together and frost cake when finished baking.

title: german slaw
directions: Slice onions and cabbage in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Bring to boil the sugar, salt, celery seed, dry mustard, vinegar and oil. Pour hot mixture over cabbage and onions.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: stuffed steak rolls
directions: Prepare bread stuffing as directed on package, adding minced onion and Italian seasoning. Spread 2 tablespoons of the stuffing on each steak and roll up like a jelly roll.
Wrap each roll in a slice of bacon. Secure rolls with wooden picks.
Grill over medium fire, turning frequently.
Rolls are cooked when bacon is crisp and meat is rare to medium done, about 20 minutes over medium-hot fire.
Makes 4 servings. Cooking time:
20 minutes.

title: velvet pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs one at a time. Continue mixing; add flavoring.
Add baking powder to flour; add to mixture, mixing well.
Then add milk.
Bake for about an hour or until done on 325° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble bread in bottom of an 11 x 9-inch greased pan.
Fry and drain sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, ground mustard, salt and pepper together, then add grated cheese.
Pour over bread and sausage.
Cover and put in the refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Break eggs into bowl and beat.
Drain salmon, remove skin and bones and flake.
Add to eggs with bread, salt and butter.
Heat milk to lukewarm, add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Place in greased 7 x 3 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet dip
directions: Cream the cheese in blender.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables such as carrots, celery, green pepper, etc.

title: bean bake
directions: Brown together hamburger, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: easy lasagna
directions: In a 2 qt., 11 x 7 baking dish spread 1 cup sauce.
Top with 3 UNCOOKED noodles, ricotta cheese, 1 cup mozzarella cheese, parmesan cheese, 1 cup sauce, remaining UNCOOKED noodles and sauce.
Cover and bake at 375 for 1 hour.
Top with remaining mozzarella cheese.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: nanny's nut roll
directions: In a bowl, combine 2 cups of graham cracker crumbs, raisins, marshmallows and walnuts.
Stir in condensed milk; mix thoroughly. Shape into a 14 x 3-inch log.
Roll in remaining crumbs.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap or foil.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix butter and cheese.
Add flour, salt, red pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Gently roll into small balls; flatten with a fork.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in cookie tin to keep crisp.
Easy. Stores and freezes well.

title: savory barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer for 30 minutes.
Baste chicken frequently with sauce.
(Chicken can be marinated in the sauce prior to cooking for extra flavor.)

title: miner's breakfast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a skillet; add potato cubes and bell pepper; brown slightly.
Add garlic to potatoes. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour eggs over potatoes and cook until eggs form soft curds, stirring constantly.
Mix in crumbled bacon.
Sprinkle grated cheese over the top.
Place skillet in oven or under broiler until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt and stir in milk in a saucepan. Boil; cook to soft ball stage when tried in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla and let it almost cool.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Add nuts and pour in greased dish.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar in large bowl and mix well by hand or with electric mixer. Gradually add dry ingredients, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pans.
Remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: chow mein noodle cookies(no cook butterscotch)
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in double boiler.
Stir in noodles and peanuts until covered with butterscotch.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let cool.
Pack between wax paper or plastic wrap.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place large size (14 x 20-inch) Brown-in-Bag in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In small bowl, combine flour, tomato paste, water and sugar.
Reserve 1/3 cup tomato sauce for meat mixture.
Pour remaining sauce in bag.
Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until transparent.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in cheese, rice, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Remove top and seeds from peppers.
Stuff with meat mixture.
Place stuffed peppers in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Make 6 1/2-inch slits in top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Spoon sauce over peppers when serving.

title: low-cal salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and mix well.
Soften Knox gelatin in water per instructions, and add to the dressing.
Whir to blend.
Chill and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt in double boiler the chocolate bar and butter; add Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shell and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a hand mixer.
Spray tube pan with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven (preheated).
Turn oven off after the 15 minutes of cooking time.
Leave cake in the oven for an additional 20 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil together the brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir in soda (will foam up).
Pour into the popcorn.
Spread on cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour out on wax paper to cool.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: The night before serving, liberally grease Bundt pan.
Separate each cloverleaf roll into 3 pieces.
Combine dry pudding mix with brown sugar and pecans.
Melt butter.
Place pieces of roll in prepared pan.
Pour melted butter over dough and sprinkle with the pudding mixture.
Place pan in cold oven and cover with tea towel. The dough rises beautifully by morning.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Invert pan on serving plate immediately after removing from oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add can of poppy seed. Pour into two regular or 4 small loaf pans, sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: cold vegetable pizza
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Spread rolls out onto pan.
Pat seams together.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool at least 15 minutes. Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayo; stir until smooth. Spread creamy mixture onto rolls, then spread vegetables and cheese over top; gently pat down.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
(Other vegetables and cheeses can be substituted for a varied flavor.)

title: oreo ice cream surprise
directions: Set ice cream out to soften.
Crush Oreos in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cover the crushed cookies with ice cream. Warm the jar of fudge under hot water if needed, then drizzle over the ice cream.
Mix the Kahlua with the Cool Whip, then top the mixture over the fudge layer.
Freeze for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: corn supreme
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Double for a crowd.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar (amount depends on sweetness of berries), cornstarch and water over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add gelatin.
Cool slightly.
Add salt.
Arrange berries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries or spoon it over berries.
Chill several hours. Top with whipped topping to serve.

title: homemade chips
directions: Cut stack of tortillas into 8 wedges each.
Spread wedges in a single layer on a baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cumin and lite salt. Bake at 375° about 10 minutes or until dry and crisp.
Monitor your chips as to not overbrown.
You might turn them after 5 minutes. Store in an airtight container.
When serving, freshen up in the microwave about one minute.
Let sit about 5 minutes before serving, or they will be soft and chewy.
Makes about 200 chips, 1 fat gram for 20 chips.

title: pickled beets from canned beets
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 10 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the corn oil and sugar together with spoon until sugar is dissolved.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture alternating with eggs and beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, chopped apples, nuts and coconut.
Batter will be thick. Put into greased and floured tube pan or 13-inch flat pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in tube pan or 45 minutes in flat pan. Cool cake in pan.
Use any dribble of icing you prefer.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water; let stand.
Mix remaining ingredients well and add oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Top with Caramel Nut Topping.

title: mom's cool whip pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip on medium speed of the mixer. When blended together, add vanilla and powdered sugar.
Blend all together until creamy, then add fruit.
Mix in fruit by hand (not mixer).
Pour ingredients into the graham cracker crust.
Put in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Make sure it's firm, then serve.
It's a quick easy tasty dessert!

title: granny smith apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix oats, sugar, flour, margarine and 1 tablespoon apple juice concentrate in small bowl.
Set aside for topping.
Put apples in large bowl.
Add spices and remaining apple juice concentrate.
Toss well.
Put apples in an 8-inch pie plate or 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with topping mix.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown and apples are done.

title: o'brien potatoes
directions: Drain potatoes from can.
Fry in deep vegetable oil until tender and browned.
Drain and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Saute onion in butter until deep brown and remove.
Add pimentos and green pepper.
Add cooked potatoes.
Cook and stir a few minutes.
Serve hot on a platter garnished with parsley.

title: cherry angel treat
directions: Beat powdered sugar and cream cheese in a large bowl until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip and cubed angel food cake.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch or 9 x 9-inch dish and top with the pie filling. Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours, then cut into squares and enjoy!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar, orange peel and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend into creamed mixture.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Soften cream cheese and butter. Mix all ingredients and roll out to 1/4-inch or less thickness. Cut with small cookie cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or 400° for 10 minutes. Makes about 40 small biscuits.

title: tostitos chip dip
directions: Layer in dish as follows:
Refried beans, mixed with a small amount of taco seasoning, sour cream, mixed with cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and top with black olive slices and chopped tomatoes.
Use as dip for "white corn restaurant style Tostitos chips".
Good for snack or party.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.
Keep in cool, dry place away from heat so as not to lose zip.
Cook with and sprinkle on anything and everything you eat.

title: easy chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken and taco sauce in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.

title: raspberry salad dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add frozen raspberries.
Stir until thawed.
Stir in applesauce.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.

title: pineapple-strawberry shortcake
directions: Grease and flour baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or 9 x 9 x 2-inches.
Prepare cake mix as directed in step 2 on package except add 1/2 cup of the topping mix to dry mix; reserve remaining topping mix.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Mix pineapple and strawberries.
Cut cake into squares; split squares horizontally.
In chilled bowl, beat whipping cream and the reserved topping until stiff.
Fill and top squares with fruit mixture; garnish with whipped cream mixture.
Makes 9 servings.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts or bacon bits.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except approximately 3 ounces of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle remainder of cheese on top for last 10 minutes. Use an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until soft dough forms.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and fluffy.
Pour over dough in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Let cool and serve.

title: the pink stuff
directions: Whip all together, then chill until set.

title: coconut cheese cake
directions: Mix 1 cup coconut, pecans and margarine (melted).
Press into 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Add vanilla and almond extract.
Beat until fluffy.
Add 3 eggs. Combine.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Beat 1 egg white; add vanilla and 1/3 cup sugar.
Fold in remaining coconut and put on top of cake.
Bake 20 minutes longer.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Mix, heat and eat.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together and bake in a shallow dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie pizza bites
directions: On cookie sheet, spread packaged rolls (seal perforations). Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the Ranch dressing with mayo and cream cheese; spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle on diced veggies and Cheddar.
Cut into small diamond shapes for easy handling.
Delicious!

title: chili con carne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and garlic in 3 quart saucepan until beef is brown.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, 1 hour. Stir in beans, heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered, stirring mixture occasionally until desired consistency, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.
Serve with warm cornbread.

title: homemade pimento cheese
directions: Grate the Velveeta cheese in a bowl.
Add pimentos and mayonnaise.
Spread on slices of bread or stuff celery sticks. Will make 8 to 10 sandwiches.

title: chopped ham and noodle bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until translucent.
Add chopped ham, noodles, olives and soup. Transfer to 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter in small saucepan.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into meatballs.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Good with spaghetti sauce and noodles.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and oil; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed.
Add egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar; gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal and buttermilk together.
Chip up onion; add to mixture.
Add water to mixture to make batter thin enough. Preheat oven to 450°.
Place a little oil in each muffin hole. Place in oven until hot.
Dip a large spoon of mixture into each hole.
Bake until brown.
Makes about 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, combine squash and water.
Cover. Microwave at High (10) for 8 minutes.
Stir after 4 minutes. Drain and coarsely chop.

title: meal in one
directions: Brown meat, onions, salt and pepper.
Pour off fat.
Add tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Add Veg-All with liquid.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: christmas jello salad
directions: Prepare lime Jell-O using package directions.
Pour into large rectangular dish, at least 11 x 17-inch.
Chill to set.
In double boiler, mix lemon Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Add marshmallows. Cook to melt marshmallows.
Remove from heat.
Dissolve cream cheese in hot mixture.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple; cool. Whip cream and fold into cooled mixture along with mayonnaise. Pour this mixture over the set lime Jell-O.
Make raspberry Jell-O according to package directions.
Cool and pour over 2 layers which have been set by chilling.
Very impressive Christmas salad served on pretty individual salad plates with lettuce leaf under.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken until tender in a large stewing pot or Dutch oven.
Remove chicken from pot (preserving broth in pot).
Remove bones from chicken and tear into bite size pieces; set aside. Bring broth back to heat; need about 8 cups of broth or 1/2 of the pot.
Add can of chicken broth to water in pot.
Add entire stick of butter.
Add 2 to 3 cups of milk.
Bring liquid level of broth up to about 3 inches from the top of the pot; bring to a boil.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and salt.
Fold all ingredients together.
Spread in floured and buttered jelly roll pan.
Put nuts on.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel.
Sprinkle towel with powdered sugar.
Roll up cake and cool.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O in boiling water; add milk, chopped celery and cheese.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour into dish and refrigerate until firm.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O in boiling water, then add cherries with juice and pecans.
Pour this mixture over first very carefully.
Let chill until firm, then cut into squares.
This is a delightful salad for any holiday menu.
Serves 8.

title: spicy apple wedges
directions: Cut each apple into sections, lengthwise.
Remove core. Combine remaining ingredients and brush on apple.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can add green or red peppers, olives, different cheeses, etc.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef; drain.
When almost done add green pepper and onion; saute.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into baking dish, cover and bake one hour.
Yield: 2 servings.
Carbohydrate 38 g, protein 28 g, fat 8 g, calories 336.
One serving = 3 meat low-fat exchange, 2 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange.

title: chocolate rum balls
directions: In large bowl, stir cookie crumbs and pecans and 1 cup powdered sugar and cocoa.
Stir in rum and syrup.
Stir until well blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or an 11 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight or place in freezer until firm, but not frozen.
Cut into squares.
Dip in flour.
Brown in oil and place in Dutch oven.
Mix can of mushroom soup with can of water. Pour over meat or use tomato sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
The squares can be made ahead and frozen.
When ready to use, do not thaw completely before baking; the squares must be firm.

title: last-of-the-turkey treat
directions: In greased casserole dish, pour all ingredients.
Mix together; cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: texas caviar
directions: Drain excess clear oil from dressing.
Mix peas, onions, bell pepper and pimento.
Add dressing, then salt and pepper.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Rinse and dry chicken breasts thoroughly.
Mix corn flake crumbs with rosemary and pepper. Dip chicken in egg whites and roll in the seasoned crumbs.
Place chicken in a baking pan sprayed with a nonstick spray. Do not crowd.
Pieces should not touch.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until crispy.

title: choke cherry liquor
directions: Make a heavy syrup out of the two cups water and 2 cups sugar. Cook this syrup.
Add choke cherries and brandy to syrup mixture in a gallon jar.
Set jar out into sun and burp every day from 3 to 4 weeks.
Do bring in jar at night and set out each day.
After all this, strain and put in bottle.

title: melt in your mouth rolls
directions: Mix butter and flour together.
Add sour cream.
Drop in ungreased muffin tins.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: avocado loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar and shortening, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Fold into sugar mixture.
Add pureed avocado and buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, walnuts and raisins. Let batter stand for 10 minutes.
Grease glass loaf pan with additional shortening.
Line greased pan with waxed paper.
Fill half full with batter.
Microwave on High for 8 minutes, turning quarter turn every 2 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes; remove to rack to complete cooling.
Repeat with remaining batter for second loaf.

title: irish coffee
directions: Put whiskey in bottom of glass or mug.
Stir in sugar and add coffee.
Top with whipped cream and serve immediately.

title: pork tenderloin casserole
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 400°.
Cook chops 5 to 6 minutes on one side with lid on halfway.
Turn over chops.
Lay potatoes on top of chops, then onions on top of potatoes.
Pour can of cream of mushroom soup over all.
Cover and cook until it begins steaming. Then turn on low heat and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: croustades(appetizers)
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in bacon grease.
Stir in Dijon mustard.
Mix with cream cheese.

title: waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar. Mix eggs, milk and salad oil; add all at once to dry ingredients, beating only until moistened. Bake in preheated baker.

title: lemon-supreme special
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together.
Next, add one egg at a time.
Bake in tube pan at 325°.

title: potato casserole 1
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Combine in large mixing bowl with 1/2 cup of the melted butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onion soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining butter with corn flakes and sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon jello mold
directions: Mix all ingredients together and fold in 2 cups Cool Whip. Pour into jello mold and let chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: white chili
directions: Cook chicken and chop.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 2 hours or so.
Great low-fat soup!

title: diet fudge
directions: Set aside 1/4 cup of graham cracker crumbs in a bowl.
Combine evaporated milk, cocoa and margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove the saucepan from heat.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, vanilla, Equal and nuts.
Mix well.
Set aside until cool enough to handle.
When mixture cools, shape into 1-inch balls. Roll the balls in the reserved graham cracker crumbs.
Store in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift and add remaining ingredients.
Beat thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: green icy punch
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup hot water.
Mix with next 4 ingredients and add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Mix well and pour into two 1-gallon milk jugs.
Freeze and take out several hours before using.
Shake and use while in the slush stage.
Add 1 bottle of Sprite to each jug of punch.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Saute onion in oil.
Add beef and seasonings and brown.
Add beans, corn, potatoes and soup.
Mix well and spoon into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with canned biscuits or mashed potatoes last 15 minutes of baking.

title: snow pudding
directions: Soften 1 envelope unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water. Stir in boiling water, sugar, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Strain and cool, stirring occasionally.
When it begins to set, beat until frothy.
Beat in 2 egg whites, stiffly beaten.
Continue beating until mixture holds its shape.
Pile in sherbet glasses and chill.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cook onions, celery and green pepper in butter until onions are yellow.
Add meat and brown.
Add small amount of cheese to tomatoes and heat until cheese is melted (keep enough cheese to cover casserole).
Add seasoning, tomatoes and macaroni to browned meat and blend well.
Pour into casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour; remove and sprinkle with grated cheese. Cover and let stand until cheese melts before serving.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple dumplins
directions: For syrup, mix first five ingredients and bring to boil. Remove from heat, add butter.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut hard-cooked eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with fork.
Add prepared mustard, lemon juice, salt, pepper and enough mayonnaise to make smooth and fluffy.
Fill egg whites with this mixture, making a rough surface.
Garnish with finely chopped chives or parsley, if desired.

title: bon bons candies
directions: Mix together and chill overnight, roll into balls, and dip.

title: pork loin (stuffed)
directions: Slice pork loin up to the bones, making pockets.
Mix Stove Top stuffing as directed.
Stuff mixture into pork loin.
Place into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until roast is done, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill; serve with chips.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; stir in pineapple juice.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Stir in pineapple and blueberries.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch pan; chill until firm.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and sugar; mix until smooth and well blended.
Spread over salad and top with pecans.

title: butterscotch blondies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat the butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; blend well.
In small bowl, stir together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in butterscotch chips and nuts, if desired. Spread in prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and center is set.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into bars.
Makes about 36 bars.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake well.
Beat eggs and add to salmon.
Mix canned soups with milk and add to first mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs. Drizzle melted butter over crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and place in roasting
pan.
Bake
1	hour, stirring occasionally. Slices of bacon may
be
added
on top halfway through baking. Serves 6 people.

title: low-fat curry dip
directions: In blender container, blend cottage cheese until smooth and creamy to make "mock sour cream."
Add lemon juice; blend well. Mix curry powder, garlic salt, sugar, horseradish, onion and vinegar.
Add cottage cheese mixture, salad dressing and yogurt; mix well.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with fresh vegetables or as topping for baked potatoes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and combine.
Grease casserole dish.
Place beans in bottom of dish and corn on top of beans.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion, cheese and salt.
Spread over beans and corn.
Melt butter and mix with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: basil jelly
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; add pectin.
Heat to a full boil, rolling hard boil for 1 full minute, remove basil leaves.
Pour liquid in hot jelly jars, seal and cool.
Delicious on meat.

title: grits and cheese casserole
directions: Cook grits, water and salt.
Cool.
Add other ingredients except cornflakes.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with cornflakes.
Dot with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sandy's chocolate cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat on high speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add alternately with sour cream to creamed mixture.
Mix on low just until combined.
Stir in water until blended. Pour into three greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: vegetable dip mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl; blend well.
Spoon mixture onto a 6-inch square of aluminum foil and fold to make airtight.
Label as Vegetable Dip Mix.
Store in a cool, dry place and use within 6 months.
Makes 1 (about 2 tablespoons) package of mix.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Combine flour, pecans and salt.
Stir into butter mixture.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 325° oven 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Roll warm cookies in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll again.
Makes 36.

title: artichoke and cheese bread(appetizer)
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Hollow out bread halves. Tear insides in bite size pieces and place in a large bowl.
Melt in saucepan the butter, Parmesan cheese, sour cream, artichokes, garlic and parsley.
Pour melted mix over the bread pieces.
Place bread pieces into bread shells. Top with grated Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese.
Wrap each half in foil and bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: date bread
directions: Cut up dates; pour boiling water over them and let cool.
Sift and measure flour; add baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add date mixture and dry ingredients. Bake in loaf pan in a 350° oven about 1 hour.

title: refrigerator sweet sour dills
directions: Slice dills in chunks.
Pour boiling water over dills and let stand ten minutes.
Rinse in cold water and discard the water. Boil and pour over pickles the remaining ingredients.
Pack in sterilized jars.
Pickles are ready to enjoy in a few days.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: microwave mississippi mud
directions: Mix together well the first 5 ingredients.
Pour in a greased microwave pan. Bake 7 to 9 minutes on High. As soon as it's finished, dot top with the Marshmallow Creme.
Put in microwave for 1 minute. Spread evenly over cake.
Spread on Chocolate Icing.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Cream the softened cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients. Serve with Social crackers.
Will be soft, more like a dip than a cheese ball.
Pretty looking as well as good tasting!!

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine onion, cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk; coat with cheese mixture.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Pour margarine over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crunch bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Layer saltines on foil lined 15 x 10-inch pan.
Boil butter and sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour or spoon over saltines.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes; watch carefully.
Remove from oven.
Immediately spread morsels over top of saltines, using the back of a spoon.
Sprinkle on chopped nuts or coconut, if desired.
Cool in refrigerator, break in pieces and freeze.
Keep refrigerated in plastic bag.

title: homemade "windex"
directions: Add enough water to make a gallon.
Very economical!

title: cheddar-squash bake
directions: Scrub squash; cut off ends.
Do not peel. Slice to make 6 cups.
Cook, covered, in small amount of boiling, salted water until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Sprinkle with salt. Reserve a few slices for garnish.
Mix sour cream, egg yolks and flour.
Fold in egg whites.

title: refreshing jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add 7-Up and jell slightly.
Add applesauce.
Finish jelling.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Line with layer of graham crackers (whole crackers fit fine).
Mix pudding with milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour half of mixture over crackers.
Place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour remaining pudding over and cover with third layer of crackers. Refrigerate 2 hours, then frost.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops.
Put in casserole dish and add soup.
Cook at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: pecan praline candy
directions: Combine sugars, syrup, water and salt.
Cook over low heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, add vanilla and pecans. Stir about 1 minute.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
(Peanuts can be substituted for pecans.)

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Mix in nuts and bananas. Make a well in dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture all at once. Stir enough to just moisten dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook spinach.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Parboil shells (see back of box) and drain.
Mix egg, cottage cheese, 1/2 of browned hamburger, 1/2 of spinach, pepper and garlic salt.
Mix all together in medium bowl.
Add more meat or spinach (if needed) or egg.
Stuff mix with teaspoon into shells and place in 13 x 9-inch brownie pan.
Cover with Ragu (open jar in fridge and new jar over oven).
Dice Mozzarella and place on top sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecued hot peppers
directions: Wash peppers and slice. Bring rest of ingredients to boil and simmer. Place peppers into marinade in mixture. Seal in pint jars.

title: pepper relish
directions: Remove the seeds from peppers.
Put vegetables through a food chopper or food processor.
Put vegetables in a saucepan, cover with boiling water, then drain.
Cover with cold water and bring to the boiling point; drain again.
Add vinegar, salt, sugar and celery seed.
Cook 10 minutes.
Taste and adjust seasonings.

title: lemonade punch
