directions: Combine lemonade concentrate (no water added) with orange juice.
Add soda.
Garnish with orange slices.
Serve over ice.

title: pasticchio
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on package.
Drain. Stir in 1 beaten egg, 1/4 cup milk and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese. Set aside.
In skillet, cook ground beef and onion until meat is lightly browned and onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, cinnamon, nutmeg, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast and flour together well.
Stir 2 1/2 cups hot water, let rise until double in size.
Cut dough in half. Take first half and roll into rectangle on floured surface. Spread with melted oleo.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and raisins, if desired.
Roll in jelly roll fashion and cut into 2-inch slices.
Place on baking sheet, cut side down.
Repeat with second half.
Let rise in baking pan until double.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour juice from pineapple chunks into mixing bowl.
Add pudding mix and stir well.	Add
pineapple	chunks	and
stir. Drain mandarin oranges and	cherries,
then
add
oranges
and cherries to pudding mix.
Slice and add bananas.

title: pear cake
directions: Add sugar to the grated pears and let set 20 minutes.
Beat eggs with oil and let set.
Measure flour, soda and salt together. Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in Bundt pan for 1 hour or until done.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: cole slaw
directions: Sliced cabbage or chop in a food processor.
Place a layer in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with a tablespoon of sugar.
Continue until all the cabbage is used, alternating the cabbage with the sugar.
Place on a plate, upside down, on top of the cabbage; cover the bowl with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir in the Miracle Whip before serving.
Very easy and very good, but must be made a day head.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk in boiler on stove until forms a soft ball.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered dish. Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and spread with margarine while hot.
Arrange bread in a buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and raisins. Stir salt and all but 2 tablespoons of sugar with the eggs.
Add milk and stir to mix well.
Pour over toast; let stand 10 minutes. Mix cinnamon with the remaining sugar and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pace gunpowder dip
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients. Cook in a crock-pot until melted.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: swiss stuffed pork chops(serves 4)
directions: Preparation time:
20 minutes; cooking time:
1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christmas smells
directions: Add water to ingredients.
Warm over low heat for several hours, adding water as needed.

title: chocolate-chip walnut pie
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except pie shell, until blended.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes or until golden brown and set, but still moist.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Combine all ingredients in a casserole and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best baby-back ribs
directions: Place ribs bone side down in a large roasting pan.
Combine garlic powder, salt and pepper; sprinkle over ribs.
Top with sliced onion.
Cover tightly and bake 350 degrees for 2 1/2 hours. In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Drain fat from pan; discard sliced onion.
Brush ribs with half of barbecue sauce.
Cover and bake 30 minutes longer or until ribs are tender. Serve with remaining sauce.

title: creamed peas and pearl onions
directions: Slice bacon into 1/4 inch strips.
In a
heavy bottomed skillet, fry bacon strips until crisp.
Remove bacon and retain grease in skillet.

title: frontier hominy
directions: Saute onions and peppers in 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Add beef and cook until pink disappears.
Add hominy, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons of margarine in a small pan.
Stir with flour, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook and stir constantly until cheese is melted.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: everbest fruit cobbler(microwave)
directions: In 8-inch square or round glass baking dish, arrange pie filling evenly.
Sprinkle evenly with cake mix.
Dot butter slices evenly over mixture.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts and sprinkle over top.
Cook 9 to 11 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Rest 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pizza dough
directions: Soften yeast in two tablespoons water; add remaining water and flour, mixed with salt, until a bread-like dough is formed.
Let rise until almost double; punch down and stretch over the bottom of a buttered pizza pan or cookie sheet with buttered fingers. Add your favorite pizza filling and bake at 400° until done.

title: orange rice with tenderloins
directions: Heat large skillet.
Add oil and chicken.
Saute until tender. Remove chicken and set aside.
In same skillet melt margarine and saute celery.
Stir in orange slices, chicken, rice, almonds and salt.
Toss together until all heated.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: jackie ybos' homemade chili
directions: Place ground beef into pot and cook until brown.
Add onion, salt, pepper, chili powder, flour and comino.
Mix well while cooking.
Allow flour to cook for a few minutes with the other ingredients.
Add tomato sauce and 4 or 5 cups of hot water or to the consistency that you want it to be.

title: pumpkin dessert squares
directions: Mix together and press into greased (bottom only) 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form into a ball.
Roll in chopped parsley or pecans.

title: elderberry pie filling
directions: Pour enough water in a pan to cover elderberries.
Boil for 15 minutes.
Add sugar; heat to boiling.
Add vinegar.
Thicken as you would for gravy (mix water and flour); make it thick.
Stir in milk.
Chill overnight.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Chop potatoes, carrots and onions for soup and cover with water or leftover broth to cook. When tender, add the rest of the ingredients and simmer 20 minutes. You may substitute turkey chunks from your holiday meal and save vegetables in a "soup carton, " until you have the right proportions. Serves 4 to 5.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast almonds in 350° oven on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: taco casserole
directions: In microwave-safe 2-quart casserole dish, spread beans; cover with mixture of ground beef and taco seasoning mix.
Layer cheese on top of ground beef to within 1-inch of side of dish.
Cook in microwave on High for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese has melted. Serve with sour cream and tortilla chips.

title: cupcake faces
directions: You will need 24 to 30 cupcake holders.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown beef and onions; stir in cooked macaroni.
Mix water, tomato sauce and seasoning.
Mix all together.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.
Cool cake.
Frost.

title: chicken and eggplant parmesan
directions: Beat chicken between plastic wrap until flat. Heat frying pan with olive oil. Season chicken with creole seasoning. Fry until golden. Remove chicken. Peel eggplant and cut into 1 inch squares. Dice onions. Add garlic and bay leaf. Add more olive oil and fry until soft. Add additional spices. Remove bay leaf. Add Ragu. Put chicken in foil-lined baking pan. Ladle eggplant mixture on top. Cover with mozzarella cheese. Heat to 350 degrees (until cheese melts and sauce bubbles).

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Cook together over low heat until dissolved.
Add 3/4 cup boiling water and 1/4 cup butter.
Cook over low heat until thick and creamy, stirring constantly.

title: bud's hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine everything except corn flakes.
Mix well and put in 9x13-inch pan.
Dot top with 1/2 cup butter. Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicken parmigiana(12 servings)
directions: In a large enough frying pan, add 2 teaspoons olive oil and saute onions and garlic until golden.
Add tomatoes, sherry, bay leaf, oregano and salt to taste.
Bring to boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Season breast with salt and pepper; dip in flour, then eggs followed by the cracker crumbs. Brown breasts in cooking oil until brown on both sides.
Keep warm, if necessary in a warm oven.
Spoon some of the sauce in baking dish (9 x 13 x 2-inch).
Lay a breast down at one end of baking dish.
Top with a little sauce, then Mozzarella, a little sauce and a sprinkle of Parmesan cheese over all.
Repeat, leaving some sauce to top and sprinkling more Parmesan cheese over all.
Bake 15 minutes in oven at 400° (9 x 13 x 2-inch) or until heated through and brown somewhat on top.

title: chocolate-sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed for about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour, baking soda and cocoa; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at lowest speed of mixer just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.

title: applesauce bread pudding
directions: In a well-buttered square baking dish, layer half of the bread cubes.
Combine the applesauce with the cinnamon and nutmeg and spread over the bread.
Scatter raisins over the applesauce mixture.
Top with remaining bread pieces.
Dot with butter.
Beat together the eggs, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour evenly all over bread and applesauce.
Top with more cinnamon.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: southern hoecake
directions: Sift any quantity of meal you may desire in a pan and pour on water enough to make a batter as thick as for pancakes.
Pour enough in skillet with a little lard in it to make a thin cake. Cook slow and turn once.
(Use plain meal and add a little salt.)

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil sweet potatoes in salted water.
Drain; place in greased utility dish.
Combine flour with orange juice; add syrup. Mix well.
Pour over sweet potatoes; dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Wash and tenderize round steak.
Cut into small cubes.
Combine flour and enough salt for seasoning and dredge the meat in the flour mixture.
Add to hot oil and brown with minced onion.
Add soup and water and a few drops of soy sauce.
Cook over low heat until thickened and right before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs and stir in buttermilk.
Slowly add liquid ingredients to the dry mixture; stir until blended.
Bake on a lightly greased hot griddle until bubbles appear; turn and lightly brown on second side.
Makes 14 (4-inch) pancakes.

title: greek cornbread
directions: Melt the oleo in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan, leaving only enough oleo to coat the pan and pour the rest into the mixing bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well with a fork or spoon. Pour the batter into a pan and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
When the bread is done, top it with your favorite cheese!

title: fresh strawberry sauce
directions: Puree the strawberries in a food processor or blender until smooth.
Strain in a bowl through a sieve lined with cheesecloth to remove the seeds.
Combine the puree with the remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Makes 2 cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix green beans, salt, pepper and cream of mushroom soup in casserole dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°.
Take out of oven and top with dried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer or until onions are browned.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Add flour to cookie dough and knead with hands to combine.
Roll dough onto a round baking stone or pizza pan to 1-inch of edge.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes, then loosen from the stone.
Cool completely.
Blend cream cheese, peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Spread on cooled cookie.
Peel and slice apples.
Dip apples in soda to prevent browning.
Arrange apples on cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon and nuts.
Drizzle caramel topping over all.

title: fish curry
directions: In an open saucepan, heat oil and add onions for 1 minute and add garlic. On medium heat, stir until tender. Add tomato and stir for 3 minutes. Add spices and tomato sauce. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in sour cream and on low heat, cook for 3 minutes. Add fish; stir gently for 5 minutes. Cover and cook for an additional 15 minutes. Serve over white rice.

title: spicy szechuan noodles
directions: Soba (buckwheat) noodles can be purchased at Skagit Valley Co-op.
They are best because they absorb other flavors.
Cook soba according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse.
Mix sauce ingredients and toss with noodles and vegetables.
Garnish with toasted sesame seed if desired.
Can be served hot or cold. Make as spicy as you want with additional chili oil.

title: filled rolls(a small, rich party or holiday treat.)
directions: Heat 1/4 cup butter and milk until warm.
Mix 3/4 cup flour, salt and yeast together. add to butter and milk and beat 2 minutes. Add egg and 1/4 cup flour and beat again for 2 minutes with a spoon.
Add 3/4 cup flour and beat well.
Cover bowl and let rise until double in bulk.
Form into a ball on floured pastry cloth. Let rest 15 minutes.
Return dough to bowl.
Add 1/2 cup butter, softened.
Work with hands until well mixed.
Roll out to a thin square.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch squares.
Place on each square the following:
1 pitted date (cut small), 1/4 to 1/2 walnut (broken in 2 or 3 pieces), scant 1/2 teaspoon sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Fold corners of dough to center to make squares, covering filling. Place on baking sheet, leaving space between each roll.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until medium brown.
Remove to rack for cooling.
When cool, store in covered container.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix 1st four items together then the last four. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Don't preheat oven!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli per instructions on box.
Simmer 1 stick margarine, mushrooms and soup for 20 minutes.
Layer broccoli, then soup mixture.
Add grated cheese, then can of onion rings. Bake in casserole dish for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, 1 cup warm water and 1 cup flour.
Let rise until bubbly, then add 3 cups water, 1/2 cup shortening, 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
Add sifted flour, 6 to 7 cups, to make spongy dough.
Let rise.
Punch down and store in refrigerator until needed.
Make into rolls.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: mexicorn spoon bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet or 3-quart casserole, combine margarine, soup and yogurt; blend until smooth.
Stir in cornmeal, baking powder, corn and eggs; blend well.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 8 (1-cup) servings.

title: krispy treats
directions: Line jellyroll pan with foil.
Spray with Pam.
Heat to boiling (stir).
Pour over crackers.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients and put into a buttered baking dish.
Then spread on the topping.

title: pink squirrel salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Pour into glass serving bowl. Chill before serving.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture. Add chocolate chips to top. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes and turn over on plate.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Put all of the ingredients, except rice, in a crock-pot. Cover with water.
Cook on low all night, or at least 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with hot rice.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper in oil. Drain off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients in large pot. Bring to boil, then reduce heat to simmer and continue until cabbage is tender.
Usually an hour is sufficient.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Add butter and sugars; beat well.
Add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla, salt and baking soda in water.
Add flour and chocolate chips.
Mix well. Drop by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: easy fruit whip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and mix until smooth. Serve cold with a fresh fruit garnish.
Makes 3+ cups.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs and butter.
Bake in shallow buttered pan 20 minutes on 425°.

title: no-cook banana pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding with milk. Stir in sour cream and Cool Whip. Blend well. Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mixture, ending with pudding.
Coconut may be sprinkled on top, if desired. Chill before serving and keep refrigerated.

title: swiss veal roast
directions: Place meat, fat side up, on a rack in shallow roasting pan. Roast in a 325° oven for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove meat to platter. Skim fat from pan juices.
Add undrained tomatoes, ham, wine and dash of pepper to pan juices.
Combine cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water; stir into tomato mixture.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Serve with meat.

title: batter dip for fish fillets
directions: Mix everything together.
Use soybean oil or canola oil for best results.
Make sure oil is good and hot before frying fish. Coat each piece well.
Fry until golden brown.

title: slavonic west europe salmon cutlets
directions: After draining salmon, remove bones and skin.
Mash with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form into patties. Fry to a golden brown.
May be served with sour cream, if desired. Serves 4.

title: chocolate pecan pie bars
directions: Crust:
Grease bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat flour, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and salt until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Press firmly and evenly into pan.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mom's coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Beat well.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and soda.
Beat well. Place 1/2 mixture in buttered 9-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 topping on top.
Place remaining batter on top and sprinkle on remaining topping.

title: centennial apple butter stack cake
directions: Use a large bowl.
In separate bowl, beat 2 cups molasses and 1 teaspoon soda until molasses turns a light beige color.
Combine the dry ingredients and able consistency.
Turn out on heavily floured board and knead 1/2 of the mixture at a time.
Divide dough into 14 equal portions.
Roll each portion out to fit a round cake pan.

title: zucchini cheese puffs
directions: Cut zucchini into chunks or slices and steam until slightly tender but not mushy.
Place in greased shallow, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with the cottage cheese mixed with Jack cheese, eggs, salt and dill.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves approximately 6.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Cook rice separately.
Drain all. Add soups, cheese and broccoli.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well.
Put in dish and chill.
Enjoy the evening off.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Then sprinkle on cheese and then the potato chips.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: quick chocolate snack cake
directions: Spray a 9-inch square baking pan with a nonfat cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, using a fork or wire whisk, mix Egg Beaters, water and corn syrup.
Add to flour mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack. Spread Braum's topping on top (you will not need the whole jar).

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix.
Let set overnight before serving.
It will keep 6 to 7 days.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook meat, onions and green pepper until meat is done and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Heat through.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
When set, top with 1 can of pineapple pie filling.
Cover with a carton of whipped topping.

title: jellied green bean salad
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water.
Add vinegar and ice and stir until jello begins to thicken (about 3 to 5 minutes). Remove unmelted ice.
Fold in vegetables and pour into 4 cup mold or individual molds.
Chill until firm, about 3 hours.
Unmold and garnish with crisp salad greens and mayonnaise.
Makes 6 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 3/4 cup of sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon; set aside.
Boil 1 1/3 cups of sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and 2 sticks butter for 2 minutes.
Break each biscuit in 3 pieces and roll in first cinnamon mixture.
Place a few pieces in well-greased Bundt pan; pour a little liquid mixture over them and keep repeating until biscuit pieces and liquid are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 30 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.

title: rhubarb pie filling
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Stir in rhubarb.
Turn into a prepared pie crust. Dab margarine over top in 4 or 5 spots.
Place top crust over filling; seal.
Cover edges and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: uglees
directions: Cook together until thick.

title: cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Spread butter evenly in bottom of 9-inch pan.
Spread light brown sugar over the butter; pat it down.
Spread cranberries over the sugar.

title: pumpkin cream cheese pie
directions: Soften cream cheese & add sugar, cool whip & milk.
Blend together, mixture will be thick.
Add pumpkin, mix well and put in pie crusts.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: chicken and macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together in large bowl.
Pour into 3-quart casserole. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old fashion pudding
directions: Grease a 7 x 10-inch baking dish.
Put crumbs in dish.
Add the next four ingredients, stirring until crumbs are soft and sugar is dissolved.
Layer thin slices of margarine over this. Sprinkle with a little more sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook broccoli to crisp-tender; drain well.
Drain other vegetables; combine all ingredients except almonds.
Toss lightly, mixing well.
Turn into shallow casserole and sprinkle almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: wilma's shortbread cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter 15 minutes.
Add flour during the 15 minute mixing time.
Add vanilla.
Form dough into rolls (I use an old wax paper or Saran Wrap box, lined with wax paper). Refrigerate.
Slice thin and put a milk chocolate chip or pecan in middle.

title: trifle
directions: Make cake according to directions.
Cut in half layer of cake; 1/2 amount bananas, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 amount sliced strawberries.
Repeat layers one more time.

title: alvin's shrimp chow mein
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until onion is tender.
Add next 6 ingredients, stirring well.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer 5 minutes, stirring often.
Combine water and cornstarch, stirring until smooth.
Add to shrimp mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: julie's coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box.

Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool 15 minutes, then poke holes in cake with a utility fork. Meanwhile, combine milk, sugar and 1/2 cup coconut in saucepan. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Carefully spoon over warm cake allowing liquid to soak through holes.
Cool completely.
Fold 1/2 cup coconut into Cool Whip and spread over cake.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top.
Chill overnight.
Keep refrigerated.

title: harvest loaf
directions: Grease and flour 2 or 3 loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients at once, adding nuts and chips last.
Fill pans a little over 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes in 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.

title: grannie's chicken casserole
directions: Cook
chicken breasts.	Cut into small pieces.	Mix all ingredients
together
except cracker crumbs.
If desired, add 1/2 cup chopped celery.
Layer in casserole dish and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Cook, covered at 350° until bubbling.

title: my grandma's thunder cake
directions: Cream together one at a time the shortening, sugar, vanilla, egg yolks, egg whites, water and pureed tomatoes.
Sift together the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix dry mixture into creamy mixture. Bake in two greased and floured 8 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with chocolate butter frosting.
Top with strawberries.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly, then beat in other items.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: crustless coconut or egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into a 10-inch pie plate that has been greased with butter and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg. Blend in flour.
Shape dough into balls and place on a greased cookie sheet pan.
Use a wet fork to flatten cookies.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix with wire whisk, freeze in 1 gallon freezer.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes in 350° oven. Soften oleo and dampen crushed Ritz crackers.
Cover casserole and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cranberry catsup
directions: Cook berries 15 minutes in 3/4 cup water in covered pan. Force through a sieve.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 12 to 15 minutes or until it thickens.
Serve warm on ham, pork or turkey or store in a jar in refrigerator.
Also excellent for a dip for little smoky links.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in hot milk.
Let cool a little; add eggs, baking powder and salmon.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix marmalade, lemon juice, soy sauce and garlic. Mix cornstarch and water; stir into mixture until smooth.
Cook until mixture thickens.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a baking dish.

title: cream cheese pecan pound cake
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 c. pecans into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after each.
Add flour and salt slowly, mix well.
Add vanilla and remaining pecans. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: country casserole
directions: Chop celery, onion and green pepper.
In a large saucepan, cook in margarine until all are tender.
Stir in flour, basil and pepper.
Add milk and cook until thickened and bubbly, then cook and stir 1 minute more.
Stir in meat and vegetables.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Cut biscuits into fourths.
Place on mixture. Bake in a 400° oven for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: texas coleslaw
directions: Day before, put cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrots in mixing bowl; toss lightly.
In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth and blended.
Pour dressing over vegetables and toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: christmas morning eggs
directions: Remove crusts from bread, cut bread into cubes.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Combine eggs and milk in a large bowl; mix well.
Pour over bread cubes.
Sprinkle with cheese and seasoning.
Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs, then add all ingredients.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Pour onto pan; bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven; turn onto a tea towel (sprinkled with powdered sugar).
Roll tight and let cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop hearts, olives and chilies.
Combine all ingredients and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Use as a dip with Dorito corn chips.

title: maple barbecued ribs
directions: Marinate pork ribs overnight.
Barbecue, basting frequently. Serves 4.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients for 4 minutes; add oatmeal.
Drop by tablespoon on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: almond carob tofu pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients except slivered almonds into food processor.
(This pudding is too thick for a blender.) Stir the 1/2 cup slivered almonds into the pudding.
Spoon into individual pudding cups and chill thoroughly before serving.
Just before serving, sprinkle a few slivered almonds on top of each serving. Almonds may be toasted if desired.
Keeps 5 to 8 days in refrigerator.
Makes 4 servings.

title: black walnut cream
directions: Cook until soft ball, add nuts and cool, beat until smooth and add vanilla.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: steak
directions: Take whole deer tenderloin steak, put 5 or 6 slices of bacon in pan, a little cooking wine (red) and a little A.1.
steak sauce.
Add sliced onion and pepper.
Fry all in butter for 5 to 7 minutes on high.
Add a little Morton Nature Season.

title: spicy chicken and corn(serves 4)
directions: Cook chicken pieces in margarine over medium-high heat, stirring often until no longer pink.
Cook onion with chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Stir often.
Cover.
Cook over low heat (simmer) until chicken is done and green pepper is crisp-tender.
Stir often (approximately 10 minutes).
Enjoy!

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat yolks until
light and fluffy.
Add half of sugar, flour, cornstarch, butter,
salt and milk (both evaporated and whole). Mix well
and
heat
in double boiler until lukewarm. While heating caramelize 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour quickly into egg mixture; stir constantly until thick.
Add vanilla;	pour into baked pie shell and
cover
with
meringue.
Bake in 350° oven until brown. Let cool 2 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice in a greased casserole dish. Put cooked rice, chicken and pimiento.
Blend together; salt lightly.
In separate bowl, mix soup and 3/4 soup can of chicken broth.
Pour over casserole and mix gently.
Top with crushed Cheez-Its.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, butter, baking soda and cream of tartar together in bowl with mixer until crumbly.
Mix together eggs, milk and vanilla and add to flour mixture.
Pat dough on floured board.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter. Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown. Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk together 2 minutes. Add pumpkin and cinnamon. Mix well and stir in 1 cup Cool Whip; spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip on the top.

title: crusty beef cheese noodle bake
directions: Brown meat and onion until cooked; add remaining ingredients and heat.
Arrange in casserole dish, layer meat, noodles, sauce and place cheese on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour (1/2 hour covered and 1/2 hour uncovered).

title: margie's holupki (cabbage rolls)
directions: Wilt cabbage leaves by scalding in boiling water.
Drain and pat dry.
Cut out heavy ribs.
Saute onion with bacon until transparent.
Drain off most of the drippings.

title: my favorite cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs. Beat 4 minutes.
Mix flour, salt and soda. Stir into the creamed mixture. Add chocolate chips or M&M's.
Roll heaping teaspoonfuls of dough by hand into round balls and place onto a foil lined cookie sheet. Do not flatten.
Bake at 350° for exactly 14 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook the chicken; take chicken out of stock and pick off bones.
Put 1/2 stick margarine in stock.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: fruit pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells. Refrigerate. Try it, you will like it.

title: western mex
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onions and bell pepper.
Stir-fry 1 minute.
Add corn, tomato paste, water and macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Mix all well.
Add taco mix, salt and pepper.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: greek wedding cakes(kourabiedes)
directions: Cream the butter with electric mixer until it is light and fluffy.
Add the sugar slowly, beating all the time.
Add the egg yolk and brandy.
Sift the baking powder with the flour and fold into the first mixture by hand.
Add the chopped nuts a little at a time.
Knead gently with hands, adding a little flour to keep the dough from sticking.
Using about 1 tablespoon of dough, shape into crescents or balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake about 35 minutes in a 375° oven or until golden brown.
Watch carefully. Remove at end of baking time and allow to cool slightly.
Sprinkle heavily with confectioners sugar while warm.
These cakes may be stored when cold.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients.
Fold in strawberries.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Put in cold oven and keep door closed during cooking time.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Put all through a food grinder.
Let stand to room temperature; work together with hands.
Roll into rolls in paprika or chili powder.
Roll in pecans.
Put in refrigerator.
Serve sliced.

title: chocolate mini chip cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12
to 15 minutes.
Big batch.

title: frozen bread caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread.
Do not let rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear one loaf into pieces and drop helter skelter into pan.
Melt margarine; add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over first torn up loaf.
Tear second loaf and drop into empty spots.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Turn out onto wax paper.

title: creamy chicken primaveraroswell, new mexico
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add vegetables and pasta and water.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes, or until vegetables or crisp and tender.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Brown the chicken on both sides and drain on paper towels. Blend together all other ingredients and heat until butter and sugar have melted.
Put chicken in the pan and pour the sauce over the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and vegetable linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to pkg. directions. Meanwhile, in a large skillet, saute asparagus, mushrooms, carrot, zucchini and ham in butter until the vegetables are tender. Add cream, peas, onions, parmesan, basil, salt, pepper and nutmeg; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer for 3 minutes stirring frequently. Rinse and drain linguine; add to vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese if desired.

title: oatmeal crackers
directions: Mix together.
Add oil and honey, then enough water to make stiff.
Knead thoroughly.
Roll very thin.
Prick with a fork and mark off in squares.
Bake in slow or moderate oven at 300° until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: eastern shore sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, milk, eggs and sugar.
Beat at high speed with mixer.
Add flavoring.
Mix.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: great layered salad
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix in the pretzels and form into bottom crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thick. Can also be cooked in a crock-pot.

title: lemon-ginger chicken salad
directions: Stir together first 7 ingredients.
Add chicken and grapes. Toss well.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve in cantaloupe halves. Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Serves 4.

title: miniature peanut butter treats
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg, peanut butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt and add to creamed mixture.
Cover dough and chill.
Roll into small balls to fit tart pan and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently press 1 miniature peanut butter cup into each cookie. Cool in pan 10 minutes, then remove.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: festive pumpkin pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger, salt and cloves.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Blend in pumpkin, milk and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice the eggs lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash with a fork. Stir in the mayonnaise, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Stuff yolk mixture into the egg white halves.
Garnish with a sprinkle of paprika.
Makes 12 eggs.

title: crabmeat canape
directions: Mix ingredients together except muffins. Separate muffins and spread with the mixture. Put in freezer for at least 1 hour, then quarter.

title: smoked turkey
directions: Prepare grill.
Soak hickory chips in water.
Clean and dry turkey inside and out.
Salt the cavity.
Stuff neck cavity with 1 stalk celery, broken into pieces to fit, and half an onion; fasten opening with turkey pins or sew with string.
Stuff the remaining celery and onion into body cavity.
Truss.
Bend wing tips to the back.
Cover with moist paper towels and refrigerate.

title: fried rice
directions: Beat egg whites and yolks together.
In a small skillet, scramble eggs in 1 tablespoon oil.
Set aside.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Stir together salad dressing, salsa and chili powder.
Place chicken on grill or rack of broiler pan.
Brush with half of sauce.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes, turn and brush with remaining sauce.
Continue cooking until done.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine by hand or with mixer.
Add egg, mixing well.
Add lemon flavoring.
Gradually add flour until fairly stiff dough.
Roll into small balls and press on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° just until edges turn light brown.

title: oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oats, nuts and chocolate chips, if desired.
May be cooked as drop cookies or form in long rolls and chill.
Slice 1/4 inch thick and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: unstuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage and drain. Brown ground beef. Mix with onion, salt and pepper.
Mix together all ingredients. Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender.

title: bev's vegetable dip
directions: Mix until sugar is dissolved and there are no lumps.
Make well in advance (several hours at least) so sugar has time to lose its grainy texture.
Refrigerate.

title: tacos
directions: Brown meat in pan.
Add spices and about 1/2 cup water. Simmer until water is gone.
In taco shell, layer meat, onions, tomato, cheese and lettuce.
Heat and eat.

title: campground omelet
directions: Beat eggs.
Put water, eggs and desired other ingredients in the Zip Lock bag.
Make sure all air is removed from bag.
Place bag in boiling water for 13 minutes.
If a group party, be sure to put name on each bag.

title: reduced fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt one cup morsels, sugar, applesauce and margarine in large saucepan over low heat until smooth. Remove pan from heat; add egg whites and stir well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in remaining morsels and nuts.
Spread mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: jello-ice cream-pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all together.
Put in refrigerator until jelled.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients in 2-cup measure or 1-quart casserole. Stir in water.
Cook on Full power 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Blend in butter.
Cook Full power for 30 seconds or until butter is melted.
Stir halfway.
Blend in vanilla and serve.

title: crunchy puncy
directions: Dissolve the Jell-O in 9 cups of the boiling water.
Combine the sugar with the other 4 cups of boiling water and bring to a quick boil.
Add sugar and water mixture to Jell-O mixture and set aside to cool.
When cool, add lemon juice and pineapple juice. Mix well and freeze in plastic containers or milk cartons.
When ready to serve, place bucket in hot water to loosen or let set outside freezer until it loosens.
Put punch in bowl.
Add the ginger ale, 7-Up or Sprite.
The punch may be slightly broken up with a large knife, but since it does not freeze solid like ice, the soda usually makes it just right to serve.
Serves 50 punch cups.

title: french bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over this mixture, then add 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir in 6 cups of flour or enough to make soft dough.
Knead 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and let rise in a warm place 45 minutes.
Punch down and divide into 2 circular loaves.
Place on greased cookie sheet sprinkle with cornmeal.
Sprinkle the loaves with sesame seed. Make 3 slits in each loaf. Let rise 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: In double boiler, heat cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add rest of ingredients until well blended.
Serve hot in chafing dish or warming dish.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Let cucumbers, onions and salt stand together 2 hours; rinse and drain.
Mix vinegar and sugar together; stir until dissolved. Pour over cucumbers.
Mix well.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions in 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Beat eggs in mixing bowl.
Stir in milk and salt.
Add small amounts of onion rings and stir around to coat them well.
Put flour in paper bag.
With fork, pick up small amounts of onions and drop them into bag.
Shake bag to coat onions evenly.
Fry a few onion rings at a time in frying basket in deep hot oil, about 2 minutes. Drain on paper towel.

title: baked pears(good with barbecued chicken or pork chops.)
directions: Peel and slice pears into greased square pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with allspice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally, uncovered.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Mix sugar, soda, milk and syrup.
Cook until forms soft boil. Add butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to drop from teaspoon.
Add pecans and drop on wax paper.

title: eight layer jello
directions: Grease lightly a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 1 package orange jello with 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water.
Pour in pan.
Let set about 30 minutes, until nearly firm.
Make second package of orange jello, using 3/4 cup hot water and 3/4 cup condensed milk. Pour on first layer and let set 20 minutes.
Proceed with each color in same manner as first.

title: iced cinnamon biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine the first six ingredients; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in raisins.
Add buttermilk; stir just until moistened.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; knead 4 to 5 times.
Roll into 1/2 inch thickness, cut with a 2-1/2 inch biscuit cutter.
Place with sides barely touching on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425 degrees for 12-17 minutes or until golden brown.

title: tarragon shrimp scampi
directions: In skillet, heat olive oil, saute onions and garlic over medium low heat for 3 minutes, add salt, pepper and tarragon. Saute for 1 more minute; do not let brown.
Remove from heat and let cool. In large bowl, combine shrimp with the sauteed mixture and lemon juice.

Let rest at room temperature for 30 minutes. Preheat the broiler; line a large broiler pan with aluminum foil. Place shrimp on the pan and spoon the onion mixture on each. Broil approximately 4 or 5 minutes.
Shrimp will be pink and topping should be brown.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar together.
Add onion juice and stir thoroughly; add oil gradually, beating constantly with mixer until thickened.
Add poppy seed and mix in well. Chill before serving.

title: monkey bread
directions: Quarter each biscuit and put into a bag with the cinnamon and sugar.
Shake well.
Place biscuits in
a Bundt pan.

title: stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cook on low heat until meat is done.

title: always-tender pork
directions: If boneless chops are especially thick, cut them in half to make two chops.
With meat pounder or side of pie pan, pound chops to about double in diameter.
Add salt and pepper before pounding. Mix eggs and milk.
Dip chops in egg/milk mixture and then into bread crumbs to coat.
Fry in oleo until brown on one side and turn over.
Lower heat a little and brown on second side.
These will cook fast because of thinness.
Do not overcook.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll out dough.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: southern style yams
directions: In baking dish, mix yams, brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans. Sprinkle cinnamon to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until mixture is thick.
Top with marshmallows and remaining pecans. Bake until marshmallows are browned.

title: party cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave oven on 50% power for 1 minute.
Stir in Blue and Cheddar cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Microwave on Medium until cheeses are softened, about 1 minute longer.
Beat cheese mixture on low speed, scraping bowl often until cheeses are blended.
Beat on medium speed until fluffy, about 1 minute.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Using wax paper, shape cheese mixture into a 6-inch log; roll in parsley. Refrigerate until firm.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add pineapple juice and pineapple chunks.
Add cheese.
Put in a casserole dish.
Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs together and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: white fudge frosting
directions: Combine
the
sugar and milk in a saucepan;
bring to a boil. Cover
the	saucepan.
Cook
for 5 minutes; remove from heat;
add butter
and vanilla.
Cool.
Beat until thickened. Spread	on cake and sprinkle walnuts between layers and on top of cake.

title: the picasso
directions: In a blender, mix water, orange juice, cranberry juice and bananas for 30 seconds on medium speed.
Add ginger powder, protein powder and tofu; blend for another 30 seconds.
Add raspberries, grapes, Grape-Nuts, pine nuts, peanut butter, honey and vanilla; blend for 1 minute.
Makes 5 cups.

title: great cookies
directions: Mix together.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Place in large pan and bring to a boil.
Cool very good.
Mix dry ingredients in raisin mixture.
Add one tablespoon vanilla. Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add walnuts and cherries.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: quick bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit into thirds.
Roll in hands into a 4-inch stick.
Combine cereal and salt.
Roll each stick in milk and then in cereal.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain on paper towels to remove any excess fat.
Cook manicotti noodles for 5 minutes in boiling water; leave them firm enough to stuff.
Mix ground beef, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and season with garlic powder and parsley flakes to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: bacon brunch
directions: Fry or microwave bacon (crisp) and break in small pieces.
In large pan, saute onions in margarine.
Blend in flour and pepper. Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in cheese, bacon, rice, zucchini and olives.
Pour into lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish; sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove cover and bake for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.
May try to add green chilies or salsa.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion.
Combine garlic salt and salt.
Add pepper, oregano, parsley, tomato paste and sauce with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese to the meat.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Into lasagne baking dish, put 1/3 meat mixture, layer of noodles, layer of Mozzarella, layer of cottage cheese and 3 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Repeat the process, ending with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bread salad(fatoosh)
directions: Place the pita bread in the oven at 350° to crisp. Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in a large salad bowl.

title: chicken cavalatte
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter until transparent.
Melt 1/4 cup and blend in flour; stir in milk.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in all of the remaining ingredients, except rice and cheese.
Spread rice in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour chicken mixture over rice and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and browned.

title: lasagne with stir-fried vegetables
directions: For The Sauce:
Melt butter in heavy saucepan. Combine with flour and cook roux for 2 to 3 minutes over low heat.
Add milk. Stir constantly until sauce thickens.
Add Parmesan cheese. Season to taste.
Set aside.

title: pineapple stuffing for ham or pork
directions: Melt butter over low heat; stir in brown sugar.
Continue stirring over low heat until brown sugar is melted.
Remove from heat and stir in can of crushed pineapple and 1/2 cup orange juice.
Tear bread into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch nonstick pan.
Pour pineapple mixture over bread.
Mix until bread is coated evenly.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 35 minutes.
Stuffing should be moist, but not sloppy.

title: best of all strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar together and mix with lard until mixture has a mealy texture.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, only using what is necessary to make dough hold together.
Roll out.
Spread on back of pie tin.
Prick with fork and bake until golden brown.
Prepare strawberries, sweeten to taste and slightly crush.
Just before serving, break up pastry dough in pieces and mix with strawberries.
Add desired amount of rich cream.
Serve in sherbet dishes.

title: blushing peach pie
directions: Line a 9 inch pie plate with bottom pastry; trim even with edge of plate.
Set aside. In a bowl, toss the peaches with lemon juice.
Combine the sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg; add to the peaches and toss to combine.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with red-hots; dot with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry to fit top of pie.
Place over filling; trim seal and flute edges.
Cut slits in top.
Cover edges loosely with foil.
Bake at 425 degrees for 25 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and remove foil.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until crust is golden brown and filling is bubbly.
Cool on a wire rack. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat room temperature oleo, butter and cream cheese. Add sugar. Alternate flour and beaten eggs with first mixture. Add vanilla. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Put in cold oven. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: veronica's doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, melted butter or margarine and milk together. Add flour, mixed with
the salt, baking powder and nutmeg or cinnamon.
Mix until the dough is smooth and can be rolled.
Place on a floured board; roll 1/8-inch thick. Cut with doughnut cutter. Gather holes and pieces and roll together again; cut with doughnut cutter.
Cook in hot oil, turning when one side gets golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or your favorite icing.
Great on snowy mornings!

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: In saucepan, combine cranberries, sugar, orange peel and orange juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and boil gently, uncovered, 8 to 10 minutes or until skins pop, stirring once or twice.
Cool.
Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Makes 4 cups.

title: noodle hot dish
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix soup, water, cheese and hamburger mixture.
Add to noodles.
Top with layer of shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or microwave for 5 minutes to heat through.

title: cinnamon hang-ups
directions: Mix together.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out design. Use straw to cut out hole for hanging.
Dry in oven set on low, turning every 10 minutes, until dry or let them air dry for several days.

title: strawberry-orange shake
directions: In food processor, pulse berries to chop.
Add juice concentrate; puree.
Add milk and yogurt; blend.
Serves 6.
Per Serving:
134 calories, 6 g protein, 28 g carbohydrates, 0 fat, 3 mg cholesterol and 69 mg sodium.

title: potted red cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage up small.
Place the bacon fat into a pot.
Chop onion fine.
Heat pot and when bacon fat is hot, put in the chopped onion.
Add the finely chopped cabbage and cook for 30 minutes without water.
Add the apples, which have also been chopped; add the lemon juice and sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste and allow this to cook for 30 minutes more, turning it over occasionally with a spoon.
Serve at once.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs together until light.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Fold into butter and sugar mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Roll out and cut out cookies.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375°
for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium heat until it thickens.

title: sweet slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: spanish cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 9-inch round layer pans.
Cream sugar, oil and margarine until fluffy.
Add egg yolks; beat.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and pecans. Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; fold in.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove layers from pans; cool.
Fill and frost with Spanish Cream Icing.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Wash peas, cover with water and allow to soak overnight. Drain peas and cover with 2 cups of water in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Lower temperature and cook 30 minutes longer. Add red food coloring.

title: turkey paprikash
directions: Spray a large cold skillet with nonstick coating.
Heat over medium heat for 1 minute.
Add turkey slices to skillet.
Cover and cook about 3 minutes, or until heated through.
Remove from skillet and keep warm.

title: deep chocolate java cake
directions: Mix together liquids, eggs and sugar first.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into loaf pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Bake in oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kasha and mushroom casserole
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon butter in a heavy skillet and stir in kasha. Cook 10 minutes over low flame, stirring constantly.
Break the egg into the kasha and stir vigorously until all the grains are coated and the kasha is dry.
Stir in onion, salt,
and pepper to taste and the remaining butter and chicken broth.
Cover and cook over a very low flame 25 minutes.
Stir in the mushrooms.
Add a little water if too dry.
Turn into buttered casserole, cover and bake 30 minutes in an oven set at 350°.
The kasha should be tender and moist.
Serve with your favorite meat or fish dish. Serves 4 to 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings until soft.
Drain squash thoroughly.
Mash. Add onion, drippings, crumbled bacon, salt, pepper, bread and egg.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, apple pie spice and apple juice concentrate. Cook, stirring, until it begins to clear.
Stir in apples and pour into unbaked crust.
Top with the other crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until apples are done.

title: chocolate war cake creamy icing
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Just add, don't mix, next 2 ingredients.
Boil together for 1 minute last 2 ingredients.
Add to mixture and beat until smooth.

title: texas cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Add pie filling, crushed pineapple, cake mix (spread over top), chopped pecans and coconut (in order).
Melt another stick of margarine and dribble it over the top with a spoon.
Cook one hour at 325° or until it browns and the juice bubbles up around the edge.

title: super bars
directions: Beat margarine until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add oats, flours and wheat germ.
Press into
a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cloud topped peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and butter. Bring to a boil in a nonstick pan for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add morsels.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Spread into plastic wrap lined pan.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken rankin style
directions: You will need a basting mop.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Dot with butter and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry swirl
directions: Combine crust ingredients in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Sprinkle 2/3 of crust in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: apricot brandy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add desired ice.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef in 3-quart saucepan.
Drain; add spaghetti sauce and water, simmer about 10 minutes.

title: country butter without a cow
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Add wheat germ and cracker crumbs; mix well.
Beat together eggs, oil, molasses and buttermilk; add to dry ingredients.
Stir until well blended, turn into well greased and floured tall (1 pound) coffee cans.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes; cool on rack.
Carefully run knife around base of can.
Turn out of can.
Serve warm with butter or creamed cheese.

title: pizza rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; brown in skillet.
Ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano and parsley flakes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and cooked rice.
Put 1/3 of rice mixture in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/3 of meat-tomato sauce.
Continue to alternate layers, ending with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix oatmeal and boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Add from sifter: flour, soda, salt plus cocoa and oatmeal mixture.
Stir in 1/2 of chocolate chips and nuts.

title: sour cream pancakes
directions: Beat eggs first and then add remaining ingredients and mix.

title: diabetic barbecue sauce
directions: This
recipe is enough for 2 chickens.	Cover with foil and bake
at
400° for 1 hour.	One half of this recipe can be used for Barbecue Tuna (use 4 to 6 ounce can of tuna).

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In a stockpot, melt butter over medium heat.
Cook onion in butter until softened.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Debone chicken, cut into pieces.
Crumble bread in large bowl. Add all ingredients.
Pour broth from cooked chicken over all ingredients.
Bake in shallow pan about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagna
directions: Using a large Dutch oven, saute ground round.
Chop onions and combine with meat.
Brown well. Add seasonings and pizza sauce. Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Spoon the meat mixture into bottom of pan.
Lay 6 large noodles in pan.
Pour on 1/2 sour cream mixture and 1/2 of the remaining meat mixture.
Repeat process of layering noodles, cottage cheese, sour cream and meat. Top with remaining noodles. Combine grated Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Cut bread with round cookie cutter and set aside.
Break up remainder of bread and put in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: butterscotch dessert
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts. Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely. Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Spread carton of Cool Whip over all.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: fresh carrot vinaigrette
directions: Cook carrots in water until done, but still crisp, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Add rice to stock and boil until cooked.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk and flavorings.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool on wire rack. Take out of pan after 15 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and other ingredients all together, then chill it overnight.

title: sixty minute rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.
Heat milk, shortening, sugar and salt until lukewarm.
Add to yeast mixture. Stir in flour.
Cover and set in a warm place for 15 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Turn out on floured board and pat until 1-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or make in small rolls. Place in pan.
Allow to rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: oriental sugar snap pea and chicken salad
directions: Cook rotini to desired doneness as directed on package; drain and rinse with cold water.
In large bowl, combine rotini, sugar snap peas, chicken, red pepper and pineapple; toss gently.
In small bowl, using wire whisk, blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad mixture, toss gently to combine.
Refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: spiced chicken drummettes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease an
x
7-inch baking dish.
In a small bowl, combine all ingredients, except for chicken;
set aside.
Place chicken pieces	in
a
single layer in greased baking dish.
Bake for 15 minutes.	Turn each piece over. Sprinkle chicken pieces evenly with salt mixture. Bake
for
35 to 40 minutes, or until juices
run
clear
when pierced with fork. Serve hot.

title: fudge (cooked)
directions: Butter	an
8-inch
square
pan.
In a medium saucepan, combine
butter,
milk,
sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil over medium
heat,
stirring
constantly.
Boil for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, morsels, vanilla and nuts.	Stir vigorously until marshmallows and morsels
melt
and blend.	Pour into pan.	Cool; cut into squares.

title: pumpkin supreme
directions: Combine crumbs, 1 cup sugar and melted butter.
Mix well and press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine cheese, eggs and 3/4 cup sugar.
Pour over crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare pudding mix with milk; beat well. Prepare whipped topping.
Combine pumpkin, spices and 1 cup topping.
Spread on cooled crust and cheese.
Add remainder of topping and sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: gramma's irish soda bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into a large bowl.
Stir in currants or raisins.
Combine eggs, buttermilk and shortening. Then add to dry ingredients.
Turn batter into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° until loaf tests done, about 1 hour.
Remove from pan immediately.
Keep refrigerated.
Is good toasted with butter.

title: peg's sugar cookiessand tarts
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll out thin and cut with cookie cutter Brush with 1/5 c. melted butter and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Bake at 400° for 7 1/2 minutes.

title: peanut cluster
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in large saucepan.
Add Carnation and butter.
Heat to boiling over medium heat and boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter. Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 5 1/2 cup souffle dish or a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain. Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and salt with hand beater until smooth. Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into greased dish and bake until knife inserted comes out clean (approximately 1 hour).
Serve immediately.

title: maude's chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil and debone chicken, saving broth.
Set aside.
Mix flour, water and egg to make dough.
Spread on well floured surface and roll out very thin.
Slice into strips.
Bring broth back to boil and drop strips in one at a time.
Add chicken.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes until dumplings are cooked tender.
You will need to make 2 to 3 recipes of dumplings to full 4-quart pot.
Add water as needed.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade sweet-sour dressing
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil, but don't let it boil.
Blend remaining ingredients into hot mixture.
Put in blender and mix thoroughly.
Yields 1-quart plus.

title: sunday sweet potatoes
directions: Mix and place in buttered casserole.

title: apple ring pickles
directions: Peel and take out seeds of cucumber rings.
Mix pickling lime and 8 1/2 quarts of water together.
Pour over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours.
Drain off liquid; wash rings.
Soak in plain water 3 hours; drain.
Simmer rings in 1 cup vinegar, red food coloring, alum and water to cover for about 2 hours.
Drain and throw away liquid.

title: mrs. london's vegetable soup
directions: Saute leeks in butter.
Add carrots, saute 1 more minute.
Add broccoli, cauliflower, cabbage, Brussels and chicken broth and season to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Vegetables should be crisp. Sprinkle with parsley when serving.
Very tasty and good for you!

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet, medium heat.
Add chicken; cook, stirring until chicken is cooked.
Remove; drain on paper towels.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet and carrots; cook. Stir 4 minutes.
Add broccoli and garlic.
Cook; stir 2 minutes.

title: one pot noodle soup
directions: In 4-quart pot, brown meat and onion.
Add celery and parsley; add water and bring to boil.
Cover and simmer until celery is near tender.
Add remaining ingredients except corn and noodles. Bring mixture to a boil; cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in corn and uncooked noodles; cover and simmer 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine. Pour over Crispix and stir.
Put 1 cup powdered sugar in brown paper bag.
Add mixture, then one more cup powdered sugar on top and shake well.
Spread on cookie sheet until firm.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add as much orange juice as you want for your taste.
Steep in pan for at least 30 minutes.
(Really good to put in crock-pot - makes your house smell great in the cool weather!)

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut together and set in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Bake regular-size orange cake mix and cool.
Bake in 9-inch round pans.
When cool, cut into 4 layers.

title: sweet tomato relish
directions: Bring to the boiling point and cook slowly 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove the spice bag.
Makes 4 pints.

title: old fashioned bake apples
directions: Wash apples but do not peel them.
Core by taking out center from top to bottom.
Cut thin slice off apple bottoms so they will sit upright in skillet.
Melt butter in heavy skillet over moderate flame.
Place apples in pan.
Fill core cavities with maple syrup.
Dust apples with cinnamon and pinch of nutmeg.
Add water to pan.
Cover and simmer over low flame for about 20 minutes.
Apples may be served as is or with dab of whipped cream. Serves 4.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: cream cheese crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 package rolls on cookie sheet. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk.
Spread over layer of crescent rolls.
Spread the other package of crescent rolls over cream cheese layer.
Brush with egg white.
Press in sliced almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip marshmallows in melted butter.
Roll marshmallows in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Wrap a crescent roll triangle around each, completely covering the marshmallow.
Squeeze edges of dough tightly to form a seal.
Dip in margarine and place in muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from oven and drizzle with powdered sugar and chopped nuts.

title: b b q biscuits
directions: Brown meat, onions, salt and pepper. Drain grease. Add bbq sauce. Simmer 10 mins. Place biscuits in muffin cup pan. Press dough up sides to the edge of cups. Spoon mixture into cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake until biscuits are done.

title: jerky
directions: Remove all fat from meat and cut with grain into 1/4-inch thick strips.
(partly frozen cuts easier) Place meat in flat pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour over meat.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, measure sugar, shortening and salt.
Pour on the hot water and let melt.
Let cool.
Add yeast mixture and beaten eggs. Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, until dough is soft and smooth. Refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, shape in butterhorns. Let rise until double.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°, a bit longer for cinnamon rolls.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut a lengthwise slice off the top of each hot potato (scrubbed, oiled and baked at 425° for 1 hour).
Scoop out pulp with spoon, leaving shells intact.
Mash with an electric beater; when smooth, add milk, butter and seasoning.
Add egg and whip until fluffy.
Fold in pimento and cheese.
Fill shells with potato mixture.
Freeze in foil or refrigerate.
To reheat, bake in 350° oven for1 hour and 15 minutes for frozen or 20 to 40 minutes for refrigerated temperature.

title: curried tuna salad
directions: Mix curry powder into mayonnaise and toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Boil butter, syrup, water, sugar and cream of tartar to soft ball stage, then add soda.
Stir and pour over popped corn.
Bake in oven at lowest temperature 150° to 200° for 1 hour. Stir at least 3 times.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cut and peel zucchini.
Boil with onion for 5 minutes.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Cook potatoes and onion until tender.
Make a medium to thick white sauce.
Melt oleo; add flour.
Blend.
Add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until thick.
Combine with drained, cooked potatoes and onions; stir, then place in large casserole.
Top generously (1/4-inch thick) with good melting cheese (such as Longhorn).
Bake in 375° oven until cheese melts and potatoes are bubbly.

title: super bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients together by hand.
Mix remaining ingredients in double boiler.
Put half of batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour on chocolate mixture.
Add rest of batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: ham with orange-raisin sauce
directions: Place ham in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish. Cover with waxed paper.
Microcook on High for 8 to 10 minutes or until heated through, turning meat over ever 3 minutes.
Cover and keep warm.

title: hot chicken sandwich
directions: Cut crusts off bread.
Butter 8 slices of bread; place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, eggs, mushroom pieces, olives, onion and mayonnaise and spread on top.
Place last 8 slices on top of chicken mixture.
Mix together chicken soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes to brown lightly.

title: mexican salad
directions: Cook ground beef.
Cool and season in large bowl.
Chop lettuce; add chopped tomatoes.
Add all other ingredients; toss.

title: lemon rice
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, melt butter over medium-low heat. Add celery and green onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in rice and cook, stirring, for 1 to 2 minutes, coating all grains with the butter.
Stir in stock, lemon juice, lemon zest, salt and pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cover pan and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove from heat and let stand, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes.
Discard bay leaf. Add parsley and toss rice lightly with a fork to mix and fluff. Serve hot.
Makes
6 servings.

title: crullers
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add shortening and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and add enough to make a stiff dough.
Chill about 45 minutes.
Roll dough about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in strips about 3/4 x 2-inches.
Twist and fry or roll dough with your hands in the shape of a log and fry in deep fat or oil at 360° until light brown.
Drain on paper towels.
If desired, shake in bag of confectioners sugar.

title: shrimp delight
directions: Place shrimp in cold water.
Bring to a boil and remove from the heat.
Let sit 3 minutes.
Peel and clean shrimp and set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan and blend in flour.
Add half and half gradually to make a smooth sauce.
Add cheese, catsup, Worcestershire and seasonings.
Stir over medium heat until cheese has melted.
Fold in cooked rice, mushrooms and shrimp.
Spoon into a casserole dish; sprinkle with crumbs and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: simply salad
directions: Mix salad greens.
Toast together almonds and sesame seed. Add to bacon and noodles.
Stir well.
Add to dressing consisting of:

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon, and bake 1 hour at 375°. Remove from oven and sprinkle crisp bacon on top.
This is Hollon's favorite dish.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate and drain the potatoes well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
For each pancake, drop about 3 tablespoons of batter into hot oil and flatten slightly.
Fry until golden. Turn and fry on other side.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm. Serve with applesauce.
Makes about 8 or 9 pancakes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese. Add salt, pepper and flour. Work until mixture leaves bowl and hands. Roll thin. Cut in strips or use cookie press. Bake in 425° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Combine tomatoes, onions, red and green pepper and celery in a large enamel or stainless steel pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain vegetables and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients and boil 15 to 20 minutes.
Add vegetables to vinegar mixture and return to a boil for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Ladle hot mixture into 6 sterilized pint jars.
Seal immediately.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: chicken and salsa soup
directions: In saucepan, combine chicken broth, water, chicken and chili powder.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 8 minutes.
Add corn.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes more.
Stir in salsa, red peppers, garlic, onion and spices; heat through.
To serve, ladle soup into bowls.
Top with cheese.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Mix together and bake 1 hour at 350°.
(Ritz or Hi Ho crackers, crushed, make a nice topping on this.)

title: sukiyaki
directions: Stir-fry meat in conventional skillet on top of range, or using microwave oven, preheat browning dish 6 minutes.
Add meat and fry 2 to 3 minutes until well browned.
In a 2-quart glass casserole, combine celery, onion, green onion, mushrooms and bamboo shoots with meat.
Cook, covered, 6 to 8 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Rest, covered, 10 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil first four ingredients until golden brown.
Add baking soda.
Stir.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet and spread; let cool.
Break into pieces.
Store or eat.

title: "pollo en fricasi"(chicken)
directions: Heat oil over medium heat.
Saute chicken, turning frequently. Add onion, garlic and pepper.
Saute until softened.
Stir in tomatoes and boil for a few minutes.
Add potatoes, wine, salt and pepper to taste.
Let simmer until done.
Do not add water, but may add tomato sauce, if needed.
Serve over white rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain very well in colander.
Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Add broccoli (while still warm) to Velveeta cheese.
Mix well until cheese melts slightly.
Mash Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and mix with crackers.
Spread on top of casserole dish.
