Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until edges bubble and top is golden.

title: sinker sundaes
directions: Combine peanut butter, syrup and water in small saucepan. Heat slowly, stirring constantly, until well blended.
Cool. Place one doughnut in serving dish for each sundae; top with ice cream.
Drizzle with warm peanut sauce.

title: parmesan-glazed walnuts(club member: leslie jordan)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spread walnuts in shallow baking pan; toast in oven 10 minutes. Stir together butter and salt; toss lightly with walnuts. Sprinkle cheese over top; stir.
Return to oven and heat 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Combine and bake in 350° oven, uncovered, until cauliflower is tender.

title: favorite sugar cookies
directions: Cream oil, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients; blend together.
Let stand a few minutes.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Press with a glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients, then add blueberries and nuts. Pour into bundt pan.

title: sweet and sour spinach dressing
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar in small microwave bowl.
Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, stirring once or until sugar dissolves. Pour vinegar mixture into jar and add oil, celery seed, paprika and salt. Cover tightly and shake well. Chill.
Pour over salad and toss.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Cook the pudding according to the directions, using the fruit liquid in place of the liquid called for on the pudding box.
Cool and add fruit.
Serve chilled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bran bread
directions: Mix baking soda in buttermilk.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and sugar.
Stir in egg, molasses and buttermilk.
Blend well. Add bran, raisins and nuts.
Place in well-greased loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Brown the onions and celery in 1/2 cup margarine.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole with nonstick spray.
Mix together in casserole: broccoli, rice, mushroom soup, cheese and the browned onions and celery.
Butter 2 slices of bread and crumble finely; sprinkle over top of mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: open house punch
directions: Combine punch, citrus juices and strawberries.
Mix well; stir in soda.
Add punch cubes, garnish with orange slices and serve. Makes 24 four-ounce servings.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until thickened.
Mash a few of the strawberries and add to mixture.
Put whole strawberries in pie shell and pour mixture over them.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.

title: cherry winks cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Combine and cream well the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add pecans and dates. Shape into balls by level teaspoonful of dough.
Roll dough in corn flakes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with 1/4 cherry.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool on rack.

title: chocolate krispies
directions: You will need a large cookie sheet (at least 17 x 11-inches).

title: potato biscuits
directions: Stir butter into potatoes.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add honey.
Mix baking powder, sugar and flour, adding in milk as you go.
Press into a 3/4-inch pad; cut biscuits.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: rosamarina dessert(start a day ahead)
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain and rinse.
Drain and save juices from pineapple and oranges.
Combine juices with eggs, sugar, flour, salt and lemon juice.
Boil and pour over noodles. Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add cold fruit and Cool Whip. Serves at least 15 people (1 1/2 cups each).

title: no cook boil custard
directions: Mix milk and pudding mix together and beat with electric mixer for five minutes.
Add sugar, vanilla and cream ; beat again for 3 minutes.
Let set awhile to thicken.

title: littie's bacon broccoli
directions: Place broccoli in casserole dish.
Sprinkle bacon on it.
Heat 1/4 cup water, soup and cheese until it can be blended smoothly. Pour on top of broccoli and bake dish 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled squash
directions: Combine squash, onions and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain. Make a mixture of bell pepper, vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Heat over medium heat until mixture starts to boil. Add squash mixture. Bring to a boil.
Place in clean sterilized jars.

title: apple fritters
directions: Make a batter using the flour, beer and salt.
Coat slices of apples in the cinnamon and sugar mixture and allow to stand 30 minutes.
Dip the apple slices in batter and fry in the hot oil until light brown in color.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve while hot.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack firmly into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: autumn(hamburger soup)
directions: In large saucepan, cook and stir meat until brown; drain off fat.
Cook and stir onion with meat until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes; cover and simmer 10 minutes longer, or until vegetables are tender.
If canned tomatoes are used, simmer 20 minutes instead of 10.

title: bean pot
directions: Brown the hamburger, onion and bacon and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients; cook on medium heat for 3 to 4 hours in crock-pot or bake in covered dish for 40 minutes at 375°.
Good served with corn bread.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sour cream in a large casserole.
Add Jiffy corn muffin mix, kernel corn and creamed corn.
Mix well. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: easy fudge
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil 5 minutes; stir constantly. Remove from heat; immediately add chocolate bits and marshmallow bits.
Stir until chocolate and marshmallows are melted. Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread into a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: date nut bread
directions: Place dates, raisins and water in pan to boil slowly 15 minutes covered.
Set aside for cooling or even overnight.
Cream sugars and oleo; add eggs.
Beat well, then add all ingredients and flour.
Stir well.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired.
Make 4 small to medium loaves or 3 large loaves.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes, then at 300°.
Total Baking Time:
45 to 55 minutes. Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Do not overbake.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan about 1 hour.
Add sweet and sour sauce, pineapple and pea pods.
Bake an additional 1/2 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: pork chop-tomato casserole
directions: Spray
12-inch
skillet
with
vegetable cooking spray. Brown pork
chops on each side. Transfer to plate.
Place rice over bottom
of skillet. Arrange chops on top. Stack slices of onion, tomato and green peppers on top of each chop.
Sprinkle with salt and
pepper.
Pour
tomato juice over chops. Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until chops are tender.
Serves 6.

title: apple cake no. 1
directions: Cream the shortening and sugars.
Add eggs.
Sift in dry ingredients together and beat.
Add raw apples and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Ice, if desired.

title: hamburger goulash
directions: Brown hamburger in oil.
Add diced onion to saute.
Add tomatoes, green beans and basil.
Salt and pepper to taste. Simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with rice as bed for mixture.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat the butter and Crisco together.
Gradually add the sugars and cream until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time. Add the dry ingredients alternately with the milk.
Add the vanilla and stir in the nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken with dijon mustard
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Spread mustard on both sides of chicken breast.
Put flour on wax paper or in shallow dish, coat both sides of chicken with flour.
Melt butter in skillet over moderately high heat.
Brown breasts in butter on both sides. Remove to warm platter.
Pour cream into skillet and boil rapidly for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in more mustard and seasonings to taste.
Return chicken to skillet, reheat briefly with sauce.

title: chocolate caramel pecan cheesecake
directions: Unwrap caramels.
Combine caramels and milk in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat until melted, stirring often.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle toasted pecans evenly over caramel layer and set aside.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Heat Karo syrup and sugar to boiling.
Add peanut butter. Pour over cornflakes.
Stir with spoon and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Alternate in bowl with pepper and onion.
Mix together rest of ingredients.
Pour over carrots and marinate overnight.

title: cream puffs
directions: In a saucepan, combine the water and margarine and boil until the margarine is melted.
Add the flour and stir until the mixture falls away from the sides of the pan.
Put in a mixer bowl.
Add the eggs, 1 at a time, and mix just until blended.
Drop by the teaspoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes until golden brown.
Cut almost in half and fill with Crab Spread, or ingredient of your choice.
Serve and enjoy.

title: overnight cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until real stiff.
Add sugar slowly.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips by hand.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet lined with foil.
When oven temperature reaches 400°, turn oven off.
Put cookies in oven and leave overnight.
Do not open oven door until you take the cookies out.

title: refrigerator spears
directions: In a 4-quart ice cream bucket, place cucumbers, dill, alum, onion rings and garlic.
Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour hot solution over first 5 ingredients.
Put lid on and allow to cool. Refrigerate.
Eat after 2 days.

title: strawberry icebox cake
directions: Mix and bake the first 3 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: me ma's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and egg yolks.
Sift flour three times with salt and soda and add alternately with sour cream.
Add flavoring and fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in greased and lightly floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
This is a family favorite.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Thaw and drain green beans.
Combine all ingredients, except 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: spetzels(pasta)
directions: Mix together.
Press through fryer basket (one with 1/4-inch holes) into salted boiling water.
Stir occasionally.
Will rise to surface as cooking.
Cook a few minutes, then drain.
Serve topped with spaghetti sauce or brown gravy.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high.
Add chicken, onion and bell pepper.
Cook and stir until chicken is done.
Add corn, broth and salsa; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: island chicken with plums
directions: The Farmers' Fair was held at Penn School every year in late October.
Here
farm families displayed their harvest and livestocks.
Prizes were
given
to the best harvest and guest speakers came from	the
United
States Department of Agriculture, Clemson College and other agricultural schools.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Drop by iced-teaspoonful into hot grease.
Cook few minutes until brown.

title: chicken veronique
directions: Rub chicken well with half of a lemon; sprinkle with salt. Let dry on rack for 15 minutes.
Heat butter in a skillet until bubbly.
Brown chicken in butter (about 10 minutes), turning with tongs.
Pour in Sauterne; spoon sauce over chicken.
Cover; simmer until chicken is tender (30 to 35 minutes).
About 3 minutes before end of cooking, add seedless green grapes.
Dash generously with paprika.
Pass the sauce in a bowl.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, saute zucchini and onion in butter until tender (about 10 minutes). Stir in seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta and Mozzarella with egg and seasonings.
Add spinach and mix well.
Line pan with layer of sauce, uncooked lasagna noodles, cheese mixture and sauce.
Continue to layer, finishing with sauce and remaining cheese.
(You may use extra Mozzarella, if desired.)
Pour water gently around edge.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: In large bowl, blend cake mix, eggs, pudding mix and oil.
Add sour cream.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Fold in chips.
Mix well.
The batter will be thick.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches including syrup in bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Have butter at room temperature.
Cream with sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add flour mixture and sour cream to the creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Bake in well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool.

title: diabetic spice cookies
directions: Combine water, shortening, raisins, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat in salt and soda.
Add sweetener, flour and baking powder.
Blend all together and drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.
Freezes well.

title: backbones and rice
directions: Put ribs, celery, onions, salt, pepper and water in a large covered pot and cook on high until it boils.
Cut heat to low; cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours until meat falls off the bones. Allow to cool enough to handle.
Remove the meat from the bones and put in another covered saucepan.
Add the rice and 4 1/2 cups of the stock with the celery and onions.
Taste stock for salt and add more to taste.
Cover and simmer on low heat until rice is done and liquid is absorbed.
Check from time to time and add a little more stock if rice is not done and all liquid has been absorbed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mother's homemade bread
directions: Mix together brown sugar, All-Bran, oil and boiling water. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
To sugar mixture, add eggs, yeast, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Add flour to mixture as needed for "proper feel".
Refrigerate for several hours.
Punch holes in mixture periodically.
Divide dough and place in greased loaf pans.
Brush oil on top of loaves and cover with towel.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix in order given and bake in loaf pan at 350° until done.

title: quick company rolls
directions: Scald milk; add sugar and salt and stir well. Cool to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water. Add to cooled mixture. Then add flour; beat until smooth. Add egg, then add shortening. Add enough flour to make stiff dough (about 2 1/2 cups); knead on floured board until satiny. Shape into ball and place in greased bowl. Grease top of dough; cover and place in refrigerator. Will keep 3 to 4 days.

title: powdered sugar pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour and flavorings.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in food processor until it looks like dirt.
Set aside.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter and 1 cup whipped topping.
Make pudding and add to mixture.
Fold in whipped topping.
Starting with cookies, layer each set of ingredients, ending with cookies.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add mushrooms and saute a few minutes.
Stir in flour and garlic salt.
Gradually add chicken broth and cream.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Add seasonings.
Combine with seafood and mix well.
Put in 4 to 5 quart casserole and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and add sherry.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Continue baking until golden and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: souper skillet pasta
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain. Add soup mix, oregano, tomatoes, and water. Bring to a boil, then stir in macaroni. Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until macaroni is tender. Stir in parmesan cheese and top with mozzarella cheese. Make about 6 servings.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, margarine, 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 1/2 cups of nuts.
Spread in rectangular Pyrex dish, forming a crust.
Bake at 350° until slightly brown.
Cool completely.
Blend 1 cup of sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cooled crust layer.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on top of second layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: romance cake
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, margarine and sugar; put in pan.
Cook for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on top of first layer
and
bake
until brown (same temperature). Slice when cold.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, baking powder and all other ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350°. This all-purpose cake is great for shortcakes, upside-down cake, coffee cakes, etc.

title: granola bars
directions: Toast oats in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine toasted oats with remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Press firmly into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until slightly brown around edges. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: homemade bread
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to hot milk.
Cool to lukewarm, then stir in two cups of flour.
Add softened yeast.
Add just enough more flour to form a moderately stiff dough.
Turn out on a lightly floured board or cloth.
Cover dough with a bowl and let rest 10 minutes.
Knead dough until smooth (5 to 10 minutes).
Shape dough into a ball and place in a lightly greased bowl turned greased side up.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled.
Punch down and let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough in half and shape into two loaves.
Place shapes loaves in greased bread pans.
Brush tops with melted shortening. Let rise in a warm place until about two inches over the top of pan.
Place on a low rack in a 400° oven and bake 35 minutes. Makes two loaves of bread.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes and then cool.
And add to rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° until done.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Bring water to boil in a medium saucepan.
Add salt and grits and cook, stirring, until water is absorbed.
Add butter, eggs, cheese garlic and Tabasco sauce; mix well.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: butter icing
directions: Cook in heavy saucepan.
Boil until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Beat until thick enough to spread on cake.

title: yoshida chicken(excellent and easy!)
directions: Spray dish with Pam.
Put chicken in bottom of pan.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with Lipton soup.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with oregano.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dutch spice cake(ontbijtkoek)
directions: Combine all the ingredients to a smooth paste.
Butter an oblong 8 x 3-inch cake tin, fill with dough and bake for about one hour in a slow oven (300°).
When cooked, allow to cool and keep in a tin or in the bread-bin for 24 hours before serving.

title: mom's soft gingerbread
directions: Mix all the dry ingredients.
Add molasses, eggs, and soda-hot water mixture slowly.
Stir but do not beat.
Bake in floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Nice and moist.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing thoroughly after each.
Add bananas, flour, soda and salt. Stir in nuts and oats.
Add flavoring.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In a heavy pan dissolve cornstarch with water.
Stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Slice bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Add pudding mix on top of bananas.
Chill 4 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and remove meat of chicken from bone.
Mix all ingredients well in bowl.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cook chicken in plenty of water. Cool and pick off bones (if whole fryer is used, this is enough for 2 recipes).
Put broth in large pan and add other ingredients.
Cook on low for about 1 hour.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Beat eggs until creamy, set aside.
Mix cornstarch, salt and pepper in bowl.
Slowly stir in chicken broth until smooth, then beat this mixture slowly into beaten eggs.
Stir in cheese, green pepper and chicken.
Pour into deep-dish pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then reduce heat to 325° and bake 30 minutes more. Serves 6

title: hiivaleipa (finnish bread)
directions: Measure hot water into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine; cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into small bowl; sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add yeast mixture and rye flour to lukewarm water mix.
Beat until smooth. Add 2 cups of white flour and mix well.
Add enough additional flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease on all sides.
Cover; let rise in warm place free from draft until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Shape into 2 loaves. Place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover; let rise in draft-free, warm place until doubled in bulk, about 40 minutes. Bake in hot oven (400°) for about 30 minutes or until done.
Bread will sound hollow when tapped on top when done.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving:

In a 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook onion until tender, stirring often. Add tomatoes with their liquid, tomato paste, brown sugar, oregano, 1 teaspoon of salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes to blend flavors.

title: helen anderson's pineapple dessert
directions: Break angel food cake in pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix pineapple with pudding, juice and all.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour over angel food pieces.
Garnish with more Cool Whip.
Can sprinkle top with nuts and more pineapple, if you wish.

title: rhubarb jam for freezer
directions: Pour sugar over rhubarb and let stand overnight.
Boil about 5 minutes, uncovered (rolling boil).
Add jello.
Blend well and remove from heat.
Put in jars.
When cool, put in freezer.
If doubling this recipe, put each batch of 10 cups of rhubarb in separate bowls and cook separately.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Combine the cream cheese and salad dressing mixing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: meat crust pizza
directions: Mix and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: jello salad
directions: Cook on low heat
until
jello melts.
Let cool and add buttermilk.
When partially
congealed
beat good and add Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: marinated whole tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes in 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon onto tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate, turning occasionally, for at least 8 hours, but not longer than 24 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Great with ham.

title: tuna rice pie
directions: Measure rice into a 9-inch pie pan.
Bring water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and butter to a boil.
Stir into rice; cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Blend in beaten egg.
Press against bottom and sides, not above rim of pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese into rice crust; top with half of the tuna.
Repeat layers.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over tuna.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat 30 seconds.
Heat oven to 350°. Grease bottom only of 2 small loaf pans.
Pour into pans and bake about 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool slightly, loosen sides of loaf from pan and remove from pan onto wire rack.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Do not brown meat!
Mix stew beef, mushroom soup, water and dry onion mix together.
Then pour into a 2-quart casserole or bean pot.
Cover and bake at 325° for 3 hours.
Add sliced carrots and potatoes for the last 30 minutes.
This needs no thickening and has a delicious flavor.

title: elizabeth's goulash
directions: Brown onion and hamburger in large skillet.
Cook macaroni in salt water until tender; add to hamburger mixture.
Add tomato soup or juice, chili, enchilada powder, salt, pepper and grated cheese; mix well.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add water if too thick.

title: peanut butter and marshmallow toast
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon of peanut butter on one slice of bread.
Put some of the marshmallows evenly on top of the peanut butter.
Do the same to the other slice of bread.
Put both slices in toaster oven for about a minute or until light golden brown (or on a pan in oven; broil for a few seconds).
Makes 2 slices.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together; add chicken.
Let marinate for 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut stir fry with sauce
directions: Brown meat in oil, add water and vegetables; cook until tender.
Then add sauce.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: no-knead beer bread
directions: Heat oven to 375.
Lightly grease pan.
Put flour in medium bowl.
Add beer and stir with rubber spatula.
Bake for 50-55 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and mix with corn and spaghetti sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and top with lots of grated Cheddar cheese.
It is even better if cheese is placed in spaghetti mixture.
Heat until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and shape in ball. Roll in 2/3 cup chopped pecans.

title: one minute fudge frosting
directions: Mix in saucepan and bring to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.

title: cloud cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients well, adding pecans last.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes in 300° oven.
Cool.
Top with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: jean's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook for 2 hours.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together with 1/2 can of the soup to moisten mixture.
Pour other 1/2 can of tomato soup over meat loaf before baking.
Bake about 45 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole dish with butter.
Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and Cheddar cheese together.
Pour into casserole dish; top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Melt butter and drizzle butter over Ritz crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix well and keep in covered container.
Use 2 good teaspoons tea per cup of hot water.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip and milk.
Add vanilla and sugar.
Add cream cheese and peanut butter.
Mix all together.
Add bananas.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots for 30 minutes in enough warm water to cover; drain.
Cut in quarters with scissors.
Mix butter, sugar and egg together thoroughly.
Stir in water and orange juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt; stir in.
Add chopped nuts and apricots.

title: potato kugel
directions: Grate the potatoes and drain off the water.
Add the other ingredients, mixing well.
Grease a pudding dish and heat it. Then pour in mixture and bake until brown with firm crust (about 3/4 hour) in a medium 375° oven.
Makes 4 generous servings and should be served hot.

title: peanut butter pizza
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, brown sugar, butter, peanut butter, egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in flour; spread dough over a 12-inch or 14-inch pizza pan, forming a ridge along edge.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows and chocolate chips over top of dough, then continue to bake for 5 or 8 minutes or until brown.
Cool; cut into wedges.
Store in an airtight container.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Spread on tortillas, roll and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Slice and serve with salsa.

title: devil dogs(chocolate moons)
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Sift together flour with next four ingredients and combine all with 1 cup milk.
Drop by tablespoon or teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 7 minutes at 400°.
Fill cookies with Devil Dog Filling and top with confectioners sugar.
Sure to be a hit.

title: basque stew
directions: In large kettle, brown sausage over medium heat.
Add 2 cans tomatoes, sliced potatoes, celery, celery leaves, water, beef bouillon cubes, bay leaf, salt, thyme, pepper, oregano, basil and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to dry ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Cook in hot skillet until brown.

title: zesty dill pickles
directions: In bottom of jar, put 1 grape leaf (you may have to fold it up), dill seed, garlic bud and hot pepper.
Put pickles in jar and fill with vinegar solution and seal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain (should have about 3 cups of spaghetti).
Stir butter into hot spaghetti. Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust in a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Cook meat until brown.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Heat.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion, corn and soup.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until good and hot.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Put into a 3-quart saucepan the Pet milk, miniature marshmallows and orange juice.
Stir over medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Take off heat.
Stir in dates, raisins, walnuts, mixed candied fruit and candied cherries.
Stir in well a mixture of graham cracker crumbs, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Press firmly into a 5 to 6-cup ring mold or loaf pan lined with wax paper.
Cover tightly.
Chill 2 days.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: clark bar cookies
directions: Boil the sugar and corn syrup.
Add peanut butter.
Add corn flakes and stir until well blended.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Top with chocolate chips.
Put in oven for 5 minutes at 350°.
Spread chocolate and let set.
Delicious!

title: onion cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cheeses, onion and Worcestershire sauce until well mixed.
Shape into a ball and roll in parsley.
Chill. Serve with crackers.
Yield: 1 (4-inch) cheese ball.

title: lemon apple cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
Combine apples, cinnamon and nutmeg in pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over apples.
Pour melted butter evenly over dry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Serve with sauce.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix well and keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar. Gradually add milk, then add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into shells and freeze one day before serving. Drizzle with chocolate syrup.
Pies must be kept frozen.

title: korean salad
directions: For dressing mix together the olive oil, sugar, catsup, paprika, steak sauce, onion and vinegar and chill.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat together egg whites and sugar until stiff, adding sugar to egg whites slowly.
Add nuts, chips, vanilla and salt.
Mix lightly.

title: champagne salad
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Mix cheese, sugar and all other ingredients; pour into loaf pan.
Place in freezer overnight. Take out
1 hour before serving and cut into serving pieces.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mincemeat muffins
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Combine egg and milk and add to the creamed mixture.
Mix in flour and baking powder.
Fold in mincemeat.
Pour into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
This will make one dozen medium sized muffins.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Split dough into portions. Color one half of the dough red. Refrigerate the dough long enough to be able to easily remove it. Break off one piece (approximately 1 tsp. of each color) and roll into 4 to 5 inch tubes. Twist the two pieces together and bend forming a cane. Sprinkle the top with the candy cane and sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 6 to 9 minutes.

title: ranch pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover with carrots and potatoes.
Pour soup over all.
Simmer until done.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Put chocolate chips in blender and add the coffee.
Blend on high for one minute.
Add egg yolks and the creme de cacao and blend for one minute.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff.
Add the chocolate mixture and the egg white mixture and blend thoroughly until no streaks remain.
Pour into a glass bowl and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Bring syrup and sugar just to a rolling boil and remove from heat right away.
Add peanut butter and mix well. Add corn flakes and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil.

title: pancakes
directions: Place mix in large mixing bowl; make a well in center.
In separate bowl combine water and egg yolk.
Add all at once to mix; stir until flour is just moistened.
Whip egg white to soft peak stage.
Fold beaten egg white into batter.
For thinner batter, add 1 or 2 tablespoons additional water.
Bake on hot greased griddle.
Makes sixteen 4-inch pancakes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and top with nuts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend eggs and sugar; add flour.
Mix well.
Add the other ingredients, mix well.
Pour into two 8-inch buttered pie pans. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until firm.

title: oven roasted garlic potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes in a small roasting pan or iron skillet.
Drizzle oil over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic and season with salt and pepper.
Bake potatoes for 45 to 50 minutes until tender and browned.

title: emergency rice and frank skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, combine tomatoes, green pepper, franks and basil.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice. Cover pan and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Stir with fork to fluff. Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top, cover and cook over low heat 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: licking good salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water and let set slightly.
Blend cream cheese into whipped cream and add to gelatin along with nuts, peppers, cherries and pineapple.
Place in a mold and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a colander; let stand until completely thawed and excess moisture has drained off.
Combine sour cream, soup and margarine; mix well.
Add salt, pepper, onion and cheese; mix well. Blend in potatoes.
Place mixture in a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Mix cornflakes with melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 350° for about 50 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.
Assemble no more than 2 hours before it goes into oven for best results.
Serves 8.

title: "lazy days of summer" picnic punch
directions: In a large container, combine tea with pineapple juice, orange juice, lemon juice and grapefruit juice.
Add sliced cherries and reserved cherry juice.
Chill thoroughly and pour into a large jug before leaving for your picnic.

title: rolled pizza
directions: Roll dough to size of 12 x 18-inch baking sheet.
Cover with cheese and other toppings (no sauce), being careful to stay away from the edges.
Roll dough from short side, pinching ends when finished.
Toothpicks can be used to help hold together.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.
Slice and pour warm pizza sauce over.

title: cody's quiche
directions: Mix eggs, cream and spices with a whisk.
Prick pie crust. Layer cheese and bacon in shell.
Pour cream over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes to set. Serve.

title: 5-minute chili
directions: Rinse and drain black beans.
Combine all ingredients. Microwave 10 minutes.
Garnish with shredded cheese. Serve with warm tortillas.

title: summer slaw
directions: Chop and/or grate vegetables.
Then boil the brine (sugar, water and vinegar) 5 minutes.
Cool before pouring over chopped and grated vegetables.
This keeps a month in refrigerator.

title: "can" soup
directions: Brown and drain meat; add onion.
Add remaining ingredients and heat over medium heat for about an hour.

title: pizza bread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread on rolled out bread; roll like jelly rolls.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 325° on greased cookie sheet for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marjorie's cornbread
directions: Cook corn meal in water on top of stove until combined well. Add milk, eggs and salt to corn meal mixture.
Pour in greased 9-inch square pan and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: hot dogs in hot pants
directions: Heat hot dogs in water.
Dry thoroughly before dipping in batter.
Blend all ingredients except potatoes for about 20 seconds, then beat vigorously for about 1 minute.
Stir in potatoes.
Heat fat or oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Insert wooden skewers into one end of hot dog or hold with tongs.
Dip first into cornmeal mixture, then into the hot oil.
Cook about 1 minute or until batter is lightly browned.

title: italian chicken salad
directions: Place chicken breast skin side up in ungreased square 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan; cover tightly.
Bake in a 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.
Prepare with Italian dressing.
Toss with greens, tomatoes, onion and olives; arrange in radicchio cups.
Arrange chicken, salami and cheese on greens mixture.
Garnish with anchovies.
Serve with breadsticks, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add peaches with juice and sprinkle with spices; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt and milk.
Pour over peaches and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: ritzier chicken(lo-fat)
directions: Dip chicken breast halves into beaten egg whites and coat with bread crumbs.
Heat 1 teaspoon oil in frying pan on medium heat. Add half the chicken and brown lightly on both sides. Remove from pan and place in baking dish.
Repeat with remaining oil and chicken. Top with slices of Mozzarella cheese. Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons evaporated milk.
Heat remaining milk, Parmesan cheese, parsley and pepper in saucepan. Add cornstarch mixture and cook until sauce thickens.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serve immediately.
(May be prepared ahead and refrigerated for a day or two before baking, if necessary, then bake 30 minutes.)
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Mix cooked meat and sauce; set aside.
Pour a small amount of meat sauce on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line pan with uncooked lasagne noodles. Top with small amount of sauce and cottage cheese.
Layer noodles, sauce, Mozzarella and cottage cheese.
Top all with sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Make sure noodles are covered. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until noodles are fork-tender. Watch that cheese on top doesn't get too brown.

title: peach ice cream
directions: May substitute bananas or strawberries for peaches.

title: magic finger jello
directions: Dissolve unflavored gelatin in one cup of cold water and set aside.
In saucepan, bring 1 cup of water to a boil and add Jell-O. Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture.
Stir and add 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour into a lightly greased pan and set in the refrigerator until solid (about 2 hours).
Cut into squares.
Great for lunches.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add other ingredients.
Bake in greased Bundt or tube pan 1 hour at 350°.
Ice with following.

title: onion pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Break pretzels and place single layered on cookie sheet.
Melt butter in saucepan and mix in dry onion soup mix.
Spoon mixture over pretzels.
Place in oven and bake slow for 45 minutes.
Turn pretzels halfway through.

title: barbecued beef sandwiches
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain. Add onion and green pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve on buns.

title: zupfa(swiss sunday bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Mix together flour, salt and sugar in separate bowl.
Slowly add milk and yeast.
Knead by hand or with mixer with bread hook.
Let dough rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours in a slightly warm room.
Once dough is kneaded, split dough into 4 even parts.

title: gingerbread(low fat)
directions: Blend molasses, brown sugar, canola oil, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and ginger.
Stir in boiling water.
Mix in unsifted flour. Dissolve baking soda in 2 teaspoons hot water; add to batter. Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and saute until clear. Add broccoli and stir well.
Add soup.
Stir and simmer.
Add mushrooms and simmer all several minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Add rice and diced chicken.
Place all in buttered casserole.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
May want to save some of chicken broth if it becomes too dry as it's baking.

title: punch
directions: Add sugar, jello and hot water.
Add 1 quart cold water.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: easy divinity
directions: Beat frosting mix (dry), corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small bowl on low speed until blended.
Beat on high speed about
5 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Transfer to large bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar at low speed.
Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let stand about 4 hours or until firm.
Turn candies over.
Dry at least 12 hours. Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen candies.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: cousin tim rice's cheese
directions: Brown sausage, cook and drain.
Pat with paper towel.
Over low heat, melt Velveeta, grated cheese and sausage together.
Add picante sauce.
Microwaves well also.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Let stand.
When cool, cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix onion and meat into cream cheese.
Roll in chopped nuts or Ritz crackers.
Double for larger cheese ball.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and put into a buttered spring pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour; let cool for 1 hour.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and sugar in large bowl.
Stir in butter and egg.
Add flour a little at a time.
Store covered in refrigerator and use as needed.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over hot water.
Add pinch of salt to 2 egg whites beaten until foamy.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar and beat until stand in soft
peaks.
Beat in vinegar and vanilla. Fold in coconut and nuts.
Add melted chocolate.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: caesar salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together.

title: potato rolls
directions: Combine
cups
flour,
potatoes,
sugar, undissolved yeast and
salt
in
large bowl.
Heat water and butter until very warm, stir into yeast mixture.
Stir in enough remaining flour
to make
soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until
smooth and
elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes. Divide dough into 16 equal pieces, form into balls.
Place
in greased 8 or 9-inch round pans.
Cover, let rise
in warm draft free place until doubled in size, about 20 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour on rolls.
Bake in 400°
oven
for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan, cool on wire rack.
Yields 16 rolls.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Scald milk; set aside to cool.
Beat shortening and butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well. Gradually add cooled milk slowly, beating all the time.
Add vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix and softened butter.
Mix according to directions	on
box.
Pour	1/2
of
batter
into greased 13 x 9-inch
pan.
Bake	at
350° in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Melt
the
caramels
with
1/2 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over baked layer.
Top
with
1	cup
chopped
pecans and the 1 cup chocolate chips.
Pour on rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30	minutes.
Does	not need a frosting, but any chocolate frosting will make it even richer.

title: snappy glazed meat balls
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef, egg, onion, bread crumbs and salt; mix well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: baked creamed potatoes
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter for 5 minutes. Gradually add flour and milk.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be prepared ahead and refrigerated until time to bake.

title: mom's bar-b-q'd pork chops
directions: Place pork chops on the bottom of a cake pan.
Mix all of your other ingredients together, pour over pork chops.
Bake at 375 for 1 1/2 hours.
Then eat.
Yum, Yum.

title: meatballs and dumplings
directions: Prepare meatballs. Combine first 8 ingredients and shape into about 24 meatballs. Prepare gravy mix as directed on packet using 10 inch skillet.
Stir in frozen vegetables, breaking apart with fork; stir in Meatballs.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Prepare Dumplings. 4 - 6 servings.
